{"title_page": "Frank Stoker", "text_new": "{{distinguish|Henry Hugh Gordon Stoker}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2014}}\n{{Use Irish English|date=November 2014}}\n{{Infobox tennis biography\n|name                              = Frank Stoker\n|image                             = \n|caption                           =\n|fullname                          = \n|country                           = {{flagicon|Ireland|1783}} [[Ireland]]\n|residence                         =\n|birth_date                        = {{birth date |df=yes|1867|05|29}}<ref>[http://www.census.nationalarchives.ie/pages/1911/Dublin/Trinity_Ward/Westland_Row/84417/ Residents of a house 23 in Westland Row (Trinity Ward, Dublin)], [[Census of Ireland, 1911]]; Westland Row Dublin;  Retrieved on 5 March 2018</ref>\n|birth_place                       = [[Dublin]], [[Ireland]]\n|death_date                        = {{death date and age|df=yes|1939|01|08|1867|05|29}}\n|death_place                       = [[Dublin]], [[Ireland]]\n|height                            =\n|college                           =\n|turnedpro                         = \n|retired                           = \n|plays                             = \n|careerprizemoney                  =\n|tennishofyear                     =\n|tennishofid                       =\n|website                           = <!-- official web site address like this: [http://www.site.com www.site.com] -->\n|singlesrecord                     =\n|singlestitles                     =\n|highestsinglesranking             = \n|currentsinglesranking             =\n|AustralianOpenresult              =\n|AustralianOpenjuniorresult        =\n|AustralianOpenseniorresult        =\n|FrenchOpenresult                  =\n|FrenchOpenjuniorresult            =\n|FrenchOpenseniorresult            =\n|Wimbledonresult                   = 2R (1893)\n|Wimbledonjuniorresult             =\n|Wimbledonseniorresult             =\n|USOpenresult                      = \n|USOpenjuniorresult                =\n|USOpenseniorresult                =\n|Othertournaments                  =\n|MastersCupresult                  =\n|Olympicsresult                    =\n|doublesrecord                     =\n|doublestitles                     =\n|highestdoublesranking             =\n|currentdoublesranking             =\n|grandslamsdoublesresults          =\n|AustralianOpenDoublesresult       =\n|FrenchOpenDoublesresult           =\n|WimbledonDoublesresult            = '''W''' (1890, 1893)\n|USOpenDoublesresult               =\n|OthertournamentsDoubles           = <!-- adds a \"Other doubles tournaments\" title -->\n|MastersCupDoublesresult           =\n|OlympicsDoublesresult             =\n|Mixed                             = <!-- adds mixed information-->\n|mixedrecord                       =\n|mixedtitles                       =\n|AustralianOpenMixedresult         =\n|FrenchOpenMixedresult             =\n|WimbledonMixedresult              =\n|USOpenMixedresult                 =\n|OthertournamentsMixedDoubles      =\n|OlympicMixedDoublesresult         =\n}}\n'''Frank Owen Stoker''' (29 May 1867 \u2013 8 January 1939) was an Irish [[tennis]] and [[rugby union]] player.<ref name=Cotton>Cotton, p82</ref><ref name=Scrum>[http://www.scrum.com/ireland/rugby/player/764.html Player profile] on scrum.com, retrieved 27 February 2010</ref> He is the only rugby international to have won [[Wimbledon Championships|Wimbledon]].<ref name=Cotton/>\n\nStoker was Irish tennis champion (doubles) in 1890, 1891 and 1893 - 1895. In 1890 and 1893 he and [[Joshua Pim]] won the doubles in [[Wimbledon Championships|Wimbledon]].<ref name=Cotton/> He was ranked world No. 7 for 1892 by Karoly Mazak.<ref name=\"Mazak\">Mazak, Karoly (2010). ''The Concise History of Tennis'', p. 20.</ref> He was a member of Landsdowne Lawn Tennis Club.<ref>[http://tt.tennis-warehouse.com/archive/index.php/t-290903.html Joshua Pim - A fine Irish Player]</ref>\n\nHe played five times for {{nrut|Ireland}} in rugby union between 1886\u201391.<ref name=Cotton/><ref name=Scrum/> Stoker was a Forward, he played four matches in the Home Nations Championships, and one against the touring New Zealand Natives side.\n\nStoker trained as a Dental Surgeon and qualified from the [[Royal College of Surgeons of Ireland]] holding a LDS (Licence in Dental Surgery). He lived in Westland Row, Dublin and married Margaret(Rita) in 1900, they had daughters May, [[Norma Stoker|Norma]], Joan and Ruth.\n\n==Grand Slam finals==\n\n=== Doubles (2 titles) ===\n\n{|class=\"sortable wikitable\" \n!style=\"width:70px\"|Outcome\n!style=\"width:50px\"|Year\n!style=\"width:200px\"|Championship\n!style=\"width:50px\"|Surface\n!style=\"width:180px\"|Partner\n!style=\"width:180px\"|Opponents\n!style=\"width:180px\" class=\"unsortable\"|Score\n|- style=\"background:#cfc;\"\n| style=\"background:#98fb98;\"|Winner\n|1890\n|[[1890 Wimbledon Championships|Wimbledon Championships]]\n| Grass\n| {{Flagicon|GBR}} [[Joshua Pim]]\n| {{Flagicon|GBR}} [[George Hillyard]] <br /> {{Flagicon|GBR}} [[Ernest Lewis (tennis)|Ernest Lewis]]\n| 6\u20130, 7\u20135, 6\u20134\n|- style=\"background:#cfc;\"\n| style=\"background:#98fb98;\"|Winner\n|1893\n|[[1893 Wimbledon Championships|Wimbledon Championships]]\n| Grass\n|  {{Flagicon|GBR}} [[Joshua Pim]]\n|  {{Flagicon|GBR}} [[Harry S. Barlow|Harry Barlow]] <br /> {{Flagicon|GBR}} [[Ernest Lewis (tennis)|Ernest Lewis]] \n| 4\u20136, 6\u20133, 6\u20131, 2\u20136, 6\u20130\n|}\n\n==See also==\n* [[James Cecil Parke]]\n\n==References==\n* Cotton, Fran (Ed.) (1984) ''The Book of Rugby Disasters & Bizarre Records'' (Compiled by Chris Rhys. London. Century Publishing. {{ISBN|0-7126-0911-3}} )\n<references/>\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.scrum.com/ireland/rugby/story/90163.html Ireland's Greatest All -Round Sportsman?]\n\n{{Wimbledon men's doubles champions}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Stoker, Frank Owen}}\n[[Category:1867 births]]\n[[Category:1939 deaths]]\n[[Category:19th-century Irish people]]\n[[Category:19th-century male tennis players]]\n[[Category:British male tennis players]]\n[[Category:Ireland international rugby union players]]\n[[Category:Irish male tennis players]]\n[[Category:Irish rugby union players]]\n[[Category:People from Dublin (city)]]\n[[Category:Wimbledon champions (pre-Open Era)]]\n[[Category:Grand Slam (tennis) champions in men's doubles]]\n[[Category:Alumni of the Royal College of Surgeons in Ireland]]\n\n\n{{Ireland-rugbyunion-bio-stub}}\n{{Ireland-tennis-bio-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{distinguish|Henry Hugh Gordon Stoker}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2014}}\n{{Use Irish English|date=November 2014}}\n{{Infobox tennis biography\n|name                              = Frank Stoker\n|image                             = \n|caption                           =\n|fullname                          = \n|country                           = {{flagicon|Ireland|1783}} [[Ireland]]\n|residence                         =\n|birth_date                        = {{birth date |df=yes|1867|05|29}}<ref>[http://www.census.nationalarchives.ie/pages/1911/Dublin/Trinity_Ward/Westland_Row/84417/ Residents of a house 23 in Westland Row (Trinity Ward, Dublin)], [[Census of Ireland, 1911]]; Westland Row Dublin;  Retrieved on 5 March 2018</ref>\n|birth_place                       = [[Dublin]], [[Ireland]]\n|death_date                        = {{death date and age|df=yes|1939|01|08|1867|05|29}}\n|death_place                       = [[Dublin]], [[Ireland]]\n|height                            =\n|college                           =\n|turnedpro                         = \n|retired                           = \n|plays                             = \n|careerprizemoney                  =\n|tennishofyear                     =\n|tennishofid                       =\n|website                           = <!-- official web site address like this: [http://www.site.com www.site.com] -->\n|singlesrecord                     =\n|singlestitles                     =\n|highestsinglesranking             = \n|currentsinglesranking             =\n|AustralianOpenresult              =\n|AustralianOpenjuniorresult        =\n|AustralianOpenseniorresult        =\n|FrenchOpenresult                  =\n|FrenchOpenjuniorresult            =\n|FrenchOpenseniorresult            =\n|Wimbledonresult                   = 2R (1893)\n|Wimbledonjuniorresult             =\n|Wimbledonseniorresult             =\n|USOpenresult                      = \n|USOpenjuniorresult                =\n|USOpenseniorresult                =\n|Othertournaments                  =\n|MastersCupresult                  =\n|Olympicsresult                    =\n|doublesrecord                     =\n|doublestitles                     =\n|highestdoublesranking             =\n|currentdoublesranking             =\n|grandslamsdoublesresults          =\n|AustralianOpenDoublesresult       =\n|FrenchOpenDoublesresult           =\n|WimbledonDoublesresult            = '''W''' (1890, 1893)\n|USOpenDoublesresult               =\n|OthertournamentsDoubles           = <!-- adds a \"Other doubles tournaments\" title -->\n|MastersCupDoublesresult           =\n|OlympicsDoublesresult             =\n|Mixed                             = <!-- adds mixed information-->\n|mixedrecord                       =\n|mixedtitles                       =\n|AustralianOpenMixedresult         =\n|FrenchOpenMixedresult             =\n|WimbledonMixedresult              =\n|USOpenMixedresult                 =\n|OthertournamentsMixedDoubles      =\n|OlympicMixedDoublesresult         =\n}}\n'''Frank Owen Stoker''' (29 May 1867 \u2013 8 January 1939) was an Irish [[tennis]] and [[rugby union]] player.<ref name=Cotton>Cotton, p82</ref><ref name=Scrum>[http://www.scrum.com/ireland/rugby/player/764.html Player profile] on scrum.com, retrieved 27 February 2010</ref> He is the only rugby international to have won [[Wimbledon Championships|Wimbledon]].<ref name=Cotton/>\n\nStoker was Irish tennis champion (doubles) in 1890, 1891 and 1893 - 1895. In 1890 and 1893 he and [[Joshua Pim]] won the doubles in [[Wimbledon Championships|Wimbledon]].<ref name=Cotton/> He was ranked world No. 7 for 1892 by Karoly Mazak.<ref name=\"Mazak\">Mazak, Karoly (2010). ''The Concise History of Tennis'', p. 20.</ref> He was a member of Landsdowne Lawn Tennis Club.<ref>[http://tt.tennis-warehouse.com/archive/index.php/t-290903.html Joshua Pim - A fine Irish Player]</ref>\n\nHe played five times for {{nrut|Ireland}} in rugby union between 1886\u201391.<ref name=Cotton/><ref name=Scrum/> Stoker was a Forward, he played four matches in the Home Nations Championships, and one against the touring New Zealand Natives side.\n\nStoker trained as a Dental Surgeon and qualified from the [[Royal College of Surgeons of Ireland]] holding a LDS (Licence in Dental Surgery). He lived in Westland Row, Dublin and married Margaret(Rita) in 1900, they had daughters May, [[Norma Stoker|Norma]], Joan and Ruth.\n\n==Grand Slam finals==\n\n=== Doubles (2 titles) ===\n\n{|class=\"sortable wikitable\" \n!style=\"width:70px\"|Outcome\n!style=\"width:50px\"|Year\n!style=\"width:200px\"|Championship\n!style=\"width:50px\"|Surface\n!style=\"width:180px\"|Partner\n!style=\"width:180px\"|Opponents\n!style=\"width:180px\" class=\"unsortable\"|Score\n|- style=\"background:#cfc;\"\n| style=\"background:#98fb98;\"|Winner\n|1890\n|[[1890 Wimbledon Championships|Wimbledon Championships]]\n| Grass\n| {{Flagicon|GBR}} [[Joshua Pim]]\n| {{Flagicon|GBR}} [[George Hillyard]] <br /> {{Flagicon|GBR}} [[Ernest Lewis]]\n| 6\u20130, 7\u20135, 6\u20134\n|- style=\"background:#cfc;\"\n| style=\"background:#98fb98;\"|Winner\n|1893\n|[[1893 Wimbledon Championships|Wimbledon Championships]]\n| Grass\n|  {{Flagicon|GBR}} [[Joshua Pim]]\n|  {{Flagicon|GBR}} [[Harry S. Barlow|Harry Barlow]] <br /> {{Flagicon|GBR}} [[Ernest Lewis]] \n| 4\u20136, 6\u20133, 6\u20131, 2\u20136, 6\u20130\n|}\n\n==See also==\n* [[James Cecil Parke]]\n\n==References==\n* Cotton, Fran (Ed.) (1984) ''The Book 