{"title_page": "Komalah (CPI)", "text_new": "{{refimprove|date=July 2016}}\n{{distinguish|Komala Party of Iranian Kurdistan}}\n{{Infobox political party\n| name = Komala Kurdistan's Organization of the Communist Party of Iran\n| native_name_lang = Ku\n| native_name = \n| spokesperson = [[Ibrahim Alizade]]<ref name=\"Conflit kurde\">{{cite book |title=Conflit kurde: le brasier oubli\u00e9 du Moyen-Orient |last=Bozarslan |first=Hamit |page=111 |year=2009 |publisher=Autrement |isbn=978-2-7467-1273-7}}</ref>\n| first_secretary = [[Ibrahim Alizade]]<ref name=\"Conflit kurde\"/>\n| foundation = 1984\n| ideology = [[Communism]]<br>[[Marxism\u2013Leninism]]<br>[[Internationalism (politics)|Internationalism]]\n| position = [[Far-left politics|Far-left]]\n| headquarters = [[Sulaymaniyah]], [[Iraqi Kurdistan]]\n| membership = 200<ref>{{cite book|author=Schmid, Alex P.|title=The Routledge Handbook of Terrorism Research|publisher=Routledge|year=2011|isbn=0-203-82873-9|page=654|entry=KOMOLA}}</ref><ref>{{citation|title=Iran Defence and Security Report, Including 5-Year Industry Forecasts|publisher=[[BMI Research|Business Monitor International]]|orig-year=Q1|year=2008|url=http://store.bmiresearch.com/iran-defence-security-report.html|url-access=subscription|access-date=2017-02-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170228075112/http://store.bmiresearch.com/iran-defence-security-report.html|archive-date=2017-02-28|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n| membership_year = 2001/2008\n| colorcode = Red\n| website = {{URL|http://www.komalah.org/}}\n| country = Iran\n| flag = [[File:Komala's flag.png|200px]]\n| affiliation1_title = Mother Party\n| affiliation1 = {{nowrap|[[Communist Party of Iran]]}}\n}}\n\nThe '''Komala Kurdistan's Organization of the [[Communist Party of Iran]]''' ({{lang-ku|{{lang|fa|\u06a9\u06c6\u0645\u06d5\u06b5\u06d5 \u0695\u06ce\u06a9\u062e\u0631\u0627\u0648\u06cc \u06a9\u0648\u0631\u062f\u0633\u062a\u0627\u0646\u06cc \u062d\u06cc\u0632\u0628\u06cc \u06a9\u06c6\u0645\u06c6\u0646\u06cc\u0633\u062a\u06cc \u0626\u06ce\u0631\u0627\u0646}}}}) is an [[Iran|Iranian]] Kurdish [[Communism|communist party]] active throughout the [[Iran\u2013Iraq border]]. The party is led by [[Ibrahim Alizade]]. Komala suffered a split in 2000 by Abdullah Mohtadi after ideological disagreements between him and the party's current leader Ibrahim Alizade. Abdullah Mohtadi went over to Kurdish nationalism with capitalistic and free-market ideas while Ibrahim Alizade stayed on communism. Both remain divided yet cordial. The party works as the Kurdish branch of [[Communist Party of Iran|CPI]].\n\nThe party enjoys good relations with Abdullah Mohtadi's [[Komala Party of Iranian Kurdistan]] even though they criticize each other for using the same name (Komala).\n\n==See also==\n{{Komala offshoots}}\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n*{{cite web|title=Kurdish Democratic Party of Iran (KDPI)|url=http://www.globalsecurity.org/military/world/para/kdpi.htm|website=GlobalSecurity.org|accessdate=21 July 2016}}\n{{Iranian exiled parties}}\n[[Category:1984 establishments in Iran]]\n[[Category:Banned Kurdish parties]]\n[[Category:Banned communist parties]]\n[[Category:Banned political parties in Iran]]\n[[Category:Kurdish political parties in Iran]]\n[[Category:Political parties established in 1984]]\n[[Category:Politics of Kurdistan]]\n\n\n{{Iran-party-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{refimprove|date=July 2016}}\n{{distinguish|Komala Party of Iranian Kurdistan}}\n{{Infobox political party\n| name = Komala Kurdistan's Organization of the Communist Party of Iran\n| native_name_lang = Ku\n| native_name = \n| spokesperson = [[Ibrahim Alizade]]<ref name=\"Conflit kurde\">{{cite book |title=Conflit kurde: le brasier oubli\u00e9 du Moyen-Orient |last=Bozarslan |first=Hamit |page=111 |year=2009 |publisher=Autrement |isbn=978-2-7467-1273-7}}</ref>\n| first_secretary = [[Ibrahim Alizade]]<ref name=\"Conflit kurde\"/>\n| foundation = 1984\n| ideology = [[Communism]]<br>[[Marxism\u2013Leninism]]<br>[[Internationalism (politics)|Internationalism]]\n| position = [[Far-left politics|Far-left]]\n| headquarters = [[Sulaymaniyah]], [[Iraqi Kurdistan]]\n| membership = 200<ref>{{cite book|author=Schmid, Alex P.|title=The Routledge Handbook of Terrorism Research|publisher=Routledge|year=2011|isbn=0-203-82873-9|page=654|entry=KOMOLA}}</ref><ref>{{citation|title=Iran Defence and Security Report, Including 5-Year Industry Forecasts|publisher=[[BMI Research|Business Monitor International]]|orig-year=Q1|year=2008|url=http://store.bmiresearch.com/iran-defence-security-report.html|url-access=subscription|access-date=2017-02-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170228075112/http://store.bmiresearch.com/iran-defence-security-report.html|archive-date=2017-02-28|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n| membership_year = 2001/2008\n| colorcode = Red\n| website = {{URL|http://www.komalah.org/}}\n| country = Iran\n| flag = [[File:Komala's flag.png|200px]]\n| affiliation1_title = Mother Party\n| affiliation1 = {{nowrap|[[Communist Party of Iran]]}}\n}}\n\nThe '''Komala Kurdistan's Organization of the [[Communist Party of Iran]]''' ({{lang-ku|\u06a9\u06c6\u0645\u06d5\u06b5\u06d5 \u0695\u06ce\u06a9\u062e\u0631\u0627\u0648\u06cc \u06a9\u0648\u0631\u062f\u0633\u062a\u0627\u0646\u06cc \u062d\u06cc\u0632\u0628\u06cc \u06a9\u06c6\u0645\u06c6\u0646\u06cc\u0633\u062a\u06cc \u0626\u06ce\u0631\u0627\u0646}}) is an [[Iran|Iranian]] Kurdish [[Communism|communist party]] active throughout the [[Iran\u2013Iraq border]]. The party is led by [[Ibrahim Alizade]]. Komala suffered a split in 2000 by Abdullah Mohtadi after ideological disagreements between him and the party's current leader Ibrahim Alizade. Abdullah Mohtadi went over to Kurdish nationalism with capitalistic and free-market ideas while Ibrahim Alizade stayed on communism. Both remain divided yet cordial. The party works as the Kurdish branch of [[Communist Party of Iran|CPI]].\n\nThe party enjoys good relations with Abdullah Mohtadi's [[Komala Party of Iranian Kurdistan]] even though they criticize each other for using the same name (Komala).\n\n==See also==\n{{Komala offshoots}}\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n*{{cite web|title=Kurdish Democratic Party of Iran (KDPI)|url=http://www.globalsecurity.org/military/world/para/kdpi.htm|website=GlobalSecurity.org|accessdate=21 July 2016}}\n{{Iranian exiled parties}}\n[[Category:1984 establishments in Iran]]\n[[Category:Banned Kurdish parties]]\n[[Category:Banned communist parties]]\n[[Category:Banned political parties in Iran]]\n[[Category:Kurdish political parties in Iran]]\n[[Category:Political parties established in 1984]]\n[[Category:Politics of Kurdistan]]\n\n\n{{Iran-party-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Pahlevun", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Komalah_(CPI)"}
{"title_page": "Shazam! (film)", "text_new": "{{short description|2019 superhero film directed by David F. Sandberg}}\n{{Use American English|date=August 2019}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=August 2019}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Shazam!\n| image          = Shazam! theatrical poster.jpg\n| border         = yes\n| caption        = Theatrical release poster\n| director       = [[David F. Sandberg]]\n| producer       = [[Peter Safran]]\n| screenplay     = Henry Gayden\n| story          = {{Plainlist|\n* Henry Gayden\n* [[Darren Lemke]]\n}}\n| based on       = {{Based on|[[Captain Marvel (DC Comics)|Captain Marvel]]||[[Bill Parker (comics)|Bill Parker]]|[[C. C. Beck]]}}<!-- Full credit in the film: \"Based on characters from DC Comics\" -->\n| starring       = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Zachary Levi]]\n* [[Mark Strong]]\n* [[Asher Angel]]\n* [[Jack Dylan Grazer]]\n* [[Djimon Hounsou]]\n}}\n| music          = [[Benjamin Wallfisch]]\n| cinematography = [[Maxime Alexandre]]\n| editing        = Michel Aller\n| studio         = {{Plainlist|\n* [[New Line Cinema]]\n* [[DC Films]]\n* [[The Safran Company]]\n}}\n| distributor    = [[Warner Bros. Pictures]]\n| released       = {{Film date|2019|03|15|[[Toronto]]|2019|4|5|United States}}\n| country        = United States\n| language       = English\n| runtime        = 132 minutes<ref name=\"Runtime\">{{cite web|url=https://www.bbfc.co.uk/releases/shazam-2019|title=''Shazam!'' (12A)|publisher=[[British Board of Film Classification]]|accessdate=March 25, 2019}}</ref>\n| budget         = $80\u2013100 million<ref name=\"Fuster\">{{cite web|last=Fuster|first=Jeremy|url=https://www.thewrap.com/shazam-surges-to-53-million-box-office-opening/|title=\u2018Shazam!\u2019 Surges to $53 Million Box Office Opening|website=[[TheWrap]]|date=April 7, 2019|accessdate=April 20, 2019}}</ref><ref name=preview/>\n| gross          = $366 million<ref name=BOM>{{cite web|url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=untitledmovieiv.htm|title=''Shazam!'' (2019)|website=[[Box Office Mojo]]|accessdate=October 25, 2019}}</ref>\n}}\n'''''Shazam! ''''' is a 2019 American [[superhero film]] based on the [[DC Comics]] [[Captain Marvel (DC Comics)|character]]. Produced by [[New Line Cinema]] and distributed by [[Warner Bros. Pictures]], it is the seventh installment in the [[DC Extended Universe]] (DCEU). Directed by [[David F. Sandberg]] from a screenplay by Henry Gayden, and a story by Gayden and [[Darren Lemke]], the film stars [[Asher Angel]] as Billy Batson, a teenage boy who can transform into an adult superhero, played by [[Zachary Levi]]. [[Mark Strong]], [[Jack Dylan Grazer]], [[Adam Brody]], and [[Djimon Hounsou]] also star. The plot follows Billy Batson, who is chosen by the ancient wizard [[Shazam (wizard)|Shazam]] as his new champion and receives various superpowers. Billy and his best friend [[Captain Marvel, Jr.|Freddy Freeman]] (Grazer) must discover Billy's new powers in order to stop the evil [[Doctor Sivana|Dr. Thaddeus Sivana]] (Strong) and the [[Seven Deadly Enemies of Man]].\n\nDevelopment of a live-action ''Shazam!'' film began at New Line in the early 2000s but was delayed for many years. The film went into pre-production in 2009 with director [[Peter Segal]] and writer [[John August]] and [[Dwayne Johnson]] considered to star as the villain [[Black Adam]], but the project fell through; Dwayne Johnson acts as an executive producer on ''Shazam!''. [[William Goldman]], [[Alec Sokolow]], [[Joel Cohen (writer)|Joel Cohen]], Bill Birch, and [[Geoff Johns]], among others, were all attached to the project as writers at various points. The film was officially announced in 2014, with Johnson attached to star as either Shazam or Black Adam. He would later be cast in January 2017 to lead a solo ''Black Adam'' development project, currently targeted for a December 2021 release.<ref name=\"BlackAdamRelease\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/black-adam-release-date-set-2021-1254807 |title=Dwayne Johnson's 'Black Adam' Sets 2021 Release Date |website=The Hollywood Reporter |language=en |access-date=2019-11-19}}</ref> Sandberg signed on to direct ''Shazam!'' in February 2017 and Levi was cast that October, with Angel joining the following month. [[Principal photography]] began in [[Toronto]], [[Ontario]], Canada on January 29, 2018, with most of the film shot at [[Pinewood Toronto Studios]], and [[Wrap (filmmaking)|wrapped]] on May 11, 2018.\n\n''Shazam!'' was released in the United States by [[Warner Bros. Pictures]] in [[RealD 3D]], [[Dolby Cinema]], [[IMAX 3D]], [[4DX]] and [[ScreenX]] <!--no IMAX 2D prints--> on April 5, 2019. The film grossed $366 million worldwide, making it  a box office success. The film received positive reviews from critics, with praise for Sandberg's direction and the performances of Levi, Grazer, and Angel, as well as its light tone and sense of fun.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/shazam-reviews-what-critics-are-saying-1196688|title='Shazam!': What the Critics Are Saying|author=Katie Kilkenny|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=March 23, 2019|accessdate=March 23, 2019}}</ref> A sequel is set for release on November 4, 2022.\n\n==Plot==\n<!-- Per WP:FILMPLOT, the word count in this section should be 400-700 words. -->\nIn 1974 [[Upstate New York]], young [[Doctor Sivana|Thaddeus Sivana]] is riding in a car with his father and brother when he is suddenly transported to the [[Rock of Eternity]], a magical temple in another dimension. There, the ancient wizard [[Shazam (wizard)|Shazam]] has spent centuries searching for someone pure of heart on whom to bestow his power and name as champion, after the previous champion released the [[Seven Deadly Enemies of Man|Seven Deadly Sins]] which killed the rest of the Council of Wizards. Thaddeus is tempted by the Eye of Sin, through which he hears the voices of the Sins, trapped in stone statues, promising him power if he will free them. The wizard deems Thaddeus unworthy and magically returns him to the car, where he makes a scene causing a car crash, crippling his father. The Sins send Thaddeus a message telling him to find them.\n\nIn present-day [[Philadelphia]], 14-year-old foster child [[Captain Marvel (DC Comics)|Billy Batson]] continually runs away from foster homes to search for his birth mother, from whom he became separated while at a carnival ten years prior. He is placed in a group home run by Victor and Rosa Vasquez, with five other foster children: [[Mary Marvel|Mary Bromfield]], Pedro Pe\u00f1a, Eugene Choi, Darla Dudley, and superhero enthusiast [[Captain Marvel Jr.|Freddy Freeman]]. Meanwhile, the embittered Sivana succeeds in his lifelong quest to find a way back to the Rock of Eternity. He steals the Eye of Sin, becoming the Sins' vessel, bests the wizard, and uses his newfound power to kill his father, brother, and Sivana Industries' board of directors.\n\nAt school, Billy defends Freddy from bullies and is chased into a subway, where he is transported to the Rock of Eternity. The wizard chooses Billy to be his new champion: By saying the name \"Shazam\", Billy is transformed into an adult superhero. The wizard turns to dust, leaving his magical staff behind. At home, Freddy is taken into Billy's confidence and helps him explore his newfound powers, which include super strength, speed, near-invulnerability, and electricity manipulation. By saying \"Shazam\" again, he can transform back into his normal body. Freddy posts [[viral video]]s of the new superhero, and Billy starts skipping school to use his powers to [[street performance|busk]] for money and fame, straining his friendship with Freddy. When Billy accidentally endangers and then saves a bus full of people, Sivana confronts him, demanding that he surrender his powers. Billy discovers that he can fly, and manages to escape. His foster siblings deduce that he is the superhero, and complete his search for his mother, who lives nearby. Billy rushes to see her, but is disheartened to learn that she abandoned him, having felt inadequate to raise him as a single teenage mother.\n\nSivana deduces Billy's identity and takes his foster siblings hostage. Billy agrees to transfer his powers to Sivana in exchange for their safety. They go to the Rock of Eternity to use the wizard's staff to effect the transfer, but the children follow and attack Sivana. Billy observes that Sivana becomes vulnerable when all seven Sins leave his body. Sivana pursues them to a winter carnival and unleashes the Sins upon the crowd. Remembering the wizard's words, Billy uses the staff to share his powers with his siblings, transforming them into [[Marvel Family|adult superheroes like him]]. He then breaks the staff, and his siblings battle the Sins while Billy faces down Sivana. By luring out the final Sin, Envy, Billy makes Sivana vulnerable and yanks the Eye of Sin out of his head, recapturing all the Sins.\n\nBilly and his siblings are hailed as heroes, return the Eye and the Sins to their prison, and realize they can use the Rock of Eternity as their superhero lair. Billy finally accepts his foster parents and siblings as his \"real\" family. In his superhero form, he has lunch with his siblings at school, revealing to Freddy's surprise that he has also invited [[Superman]]. In a [[post-credits scene|mid-credits scene]], the imprisoned Sivana is approached by [[Mister Mind|a talking caterpillar]], who proposes [[Monster Society of Evil|an alliance]].\n\n==Cast==\n{{See also|Marvel Family}}\n* [[Asher Angel]] as [[Captain Marvel (DC Comics)|Billy Batson]], a troubled orphan searching for his biological mother, who is chosen by the ancient wizard Shazam as his champion. David Kohlsmith plays the four-year-old Billy.\n** [[Zachary Levi]] as Shazam, the wizard's champion and Billy's superhero alter-ego, who upon saying his name possesses \"the Wisdom of [[Solomon|'''S'''olomon]], the Strength of [[Hercules|'''H'''ercules]], the Stamina of [[Atlas (mythology)|'''A'''tlas]], the Power of [[Zeus|'''Z'''eus]], the Courage of [[Achilles|'''A'''chilles]], and the Speed of [[Mercury (mythology)|'''M'''ercury]]\". Throughout his discoveries of the use of his powers, Billy and Freddy consider using other aliases for the champion, such as \"Captain Sparklefingers\".<ref name=\"Sparklefingers\">{{Cite web |url=https://screenrant.com/shazam-movie-captain-marvel-joke-sparklefists-fingers/|title=Shazam's Trailer Has A Captain Marvel Joke (But You May Have Missed It)|last=Bacon |first=Thomas |website=ScreenRant |language=en |access-date=2020-02-02}}</ref>\n* [[Mark Strong]] as [[Doctor Sivana|Dr. Thaddeus Sivana]], a scientist who was turned down as a potential champion and subsequently estranged from his family, who becomes a host for the [[Seven Deadly Enemies of Man|Seven Deadly Sins]] and Shazam's nemesis. Ethan Pugiotto plays the young Thaddeus.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Ehrlich |first1=David |title='Shazam!' Review: DC Surprises with One of the Most Fun Superhero Movies Ever Made |url=https://www.indiewire.com/2019/03/shazam-movie-review-1202052656/ |work=[[IndieWire]] |date=March 23, 2019 |accessdate=April 4, 2019}}</ref>\n* [[Jack Dylan Grazer]] as [[Captain Marvel Jr.|Frederick \"Freddy\" Freeman]], Billy's physically disabled foster brother and a fan of superheroes, who mentors Billy on the use of his newfound powers. [[Adam Brody]] plays the character's adult superhero form.<ref>{{cite web|last=Hood|first=Cooper|url=https://screenrant.com/shazam-it-jack-dylan-grazer-cast/|title=IT's Jack Dylan Grazer Joins DC's Shazam!|website=ScreenRant|date=December 6, 2017|accessdate=April 20, 2020}}</ref>\n* [[Djimon Hounsou]] as [[Shazam (wizard)|Shazam]], the last surviving member of the Council of Wizards, who has spent centuries summoning people to his temple, the [[Rock of Eternity]], in search of a \"pure of heart\" champion to whom he can pass on his extraordinary faculties.<ref>{{cite web|last=Hibberd|first=James|url=https://ew.com/movies/2018/07/10/djimon-hounsou-shazam-wizard/|title=DC's Shazam! casts Guardians actor Djimon Hounsou as the Wizard|publisher=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|date=July 10, 2018|accessdate=April 20, 2020}}</ref>\n* Faithe Herman as Darla Dudley, Billy's good-natured younger foster sister. [[Meagan Good]] plays the character's adult superhero form.\n* [[Grace Fulton]] as [[Mary Marvel|Mary Bromfield]], Billy's mature, academically-driven older foster sister. [[Michelle Borth]] plays the character's adult superhero form.<ref>{{Cite web| last=Anderson|first=Jenna|url=https://comicbook.com/dc/2018/02/05/shazam-movie-2019-grace-fulton-character-mary-marvel/|title='Shazam!': Grace Fulton Confirmed for Mary Marvel|website=Comic Book.com|date=February 5, 2018|accessdate=April 20, 2020}}</ref>\n* [[Ian Chen (actor)|Ian Chen]] as Eugene Choi, Billy's younger foster brother, an obsessive gamer and techie. [[Ross Butler (actor)|Ross Butler]] plays the character's adult superhero form.<ref name=\"ShazamFamilyActors\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.refinery29.com/en-us/2019/04/228836/who-is-the-superhero-family-in-shazam-brothers-sisters |title=Surprise! Your Fav \"OC\" & \"Riverdale\" Alums Are In \"Shazam\" |last=Bentley |first=Jean |website=www.refinery29.com |language=en |access-date=2019-04-06}}</ref>\n* Jovan Armand as Pedro Pe\u00f1a: Billy's older foster brother, a shy, sensitive boy who has trouble opening up.<ref name=\"ChenArmand\">{{cite magazine|last=N'Duka|first=Amanda|url=https://deadline.com/2017/12/ian-chen-jovan-armand-shazam-brian-astro-bradley-jr-luce-1202225185/amp/|title=Ian Chen & Jovan Armand Join ''Shazam''|date=December 12, 2017|magazine=Deadline|accessdate=December 12, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171213010829/http://deadline.com/2017/12/ian-chen-jovan-armand-shazam-brian-astro-bradley-jr-luce-1202225185/amp/|archive-date=December 13, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> [[D. J. Cotrona]] plays the character's adult superhero form.\n* [[Marta Milans]] as Rosa Vasquez, the foster mother of Billy and his siblings.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Dumaraog|first=Ana|url=https://screenrant.com/shazam-movie-cast-marta-milans/|title=Shazam Casts No Tomorrow's Marta Milans||website=ScreenRant|date=January 23, 2018|accessdate=April 20, 2020}}</ref>\n* [[Cooper Andrews]] as Victor Vasquez, Billy and his siblings\u2019 foster father.<ref>{{cite web|last=Ridgely|first=Charlie|url=https://comicbook.com/dc/2018/02/06/shazam-cooper-andrews-walking-dead-role-revealed/|title='The Walking Dead's Cooper Andrews' 'Shazam!' Role Revealed|website=Comic Book.com|date=February 6, 2018|accessdate=April 20, 2020}}</ref>\n\nThe film also features [[John Glover (actor)|John Glover]] as Mr. Sivana, the estranged father of Dr. Thaddeus Sivana and CEO of Sivana Industries.<ref name=\"JohnGlover\">{{cite web |url=https://www.cbr.com/smallvilles-john-glover-shazam-role/ |title=Smallville's John Glover Reveals His Secret Shazam! Role |date=2019-03-10 |website=CBR |language=en-US |access-date=2019-03-27}}</ref> Glover had previously starred in other DC Comics series and films: ''[[Batman The Animated Series]]''; ''[[The New Batman Adventures]]''; ''[[Superman the Animated Series]]'' as [[The Riddler]]; [[Floronic Man|Dr. Jason Woodrue]] in the 1997 film ''[[Batman & Robin (film)|Batman and Robin]]''; and [[Lionel Luthor]], [[Lex Luthor]]'s father in ''[[Smallville]]''. Natalia Safran was cast as Mrs. Sivana, though her scenes were ultimately cut from the film. Caroline Palmer portrays Marilyn Batson, Billy's biological mother. Wayne Ward and Landon Doak portray Sid the bullying brother of Thaddeus Sivana as an adult and a teenager, respectively. Carson MacCormac and Evan Marsh portray Brett and Burke Breyer, bullies at the children's school.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.memphisflyer.com/NewsBlog/archives/2019/04/01/former-memphian-writes-shazam-screenplay |title=Former Memphian Writes Shazam! Screenplay |last=Donahue |first=Michael |date=2019-04-01 |website=Memphis Flyer |access-date=2019-04-22}}</ref>\n\nDirector [[David F. Sandberg]] makes cameo appearances performing as each of the three Crocodile-Men (collaboratively assisted by Steve Newburn and Ned Morill<!--These two were listed in the credits-->), and provides the voice of the [[Extraterrestrial life|alien lifeform]] [[Mister Mind and the Monster Society of Evil|Mister Mind]] during a mid-credits sequence.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.polygon.com/2019/4/5/18295706/shazam-post-credit-scene-sequel |title=Shazam director reveals the voice behind his post-credits scene tease |last=Patches |first=Matt |date=2019-04-05 |website=Polygon |access-date=2019-04-06}}</ref> Sandberg's wife, actress [[Lotta Losten]], portrays Dr. Lynn Crosby; a researcher working with Dr. Sivana, who is killed by him.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Peris |first1=Sebastian |title='Shazam!' Star Lotta Losten Reveals First Look At Her Character Dr. Lynn Crosby |url=https://heroichollywood.com/shazam-lotta-losten-character-revealed/ |publisher=Heroic Hollywood |date=March 22, 2019 |accessdate=April 4, 2019}}</ref> Sound designer Bill R. Dean has an uncredited cameo, providing the voice for a [[Batman]] toy,<ref>{{cite web |url= https://comicbook.com/dc/2019/03/11/new-batman-toy-voice-actor-in-shazam-revealed/ |title=New Batman Toy Voice Actor In 'Shazam!' Revealed |website= ComicBook.com |language= en-US |access-date= 2019-03-11 |url-status=live |df= mdy-all }}</ref> while Ryan Hadley, Zachary Levi's stunt double, appears uncredited as a stand-in body double for [[Superman]]. Hadley's appearance is a silent cameo, where the character is only seen from the neck down, due to [[Henry Cavill]] being unavailable to film the scene.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2019/04/shazam-david-f-sandberg-director-inclusive-dc-comics-warner-bros-1202588927/ |title=\u2018Shazam!\u2019 Director David F. Sandberg Talks Going Horror To Superhero And Bringing Inclusivity To Family Narrative |last=Ramos |first=Dino-Ray |date=2019-04-05 |website=Deadline Hollywood |access-date=2019-04-06}}</ref> [[Dwayne Johnson]]'s likeness is used for the [[Mysticism|mystic-generated]] [[Holography|holograph]] of [[Black Adam|Teth-Adam]], which the wizard Shazam conjures while teaching Billy the history of the Rock of Eternity, the Seven Realms of Magic, and his previous Champion.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cbr.com/shazam-movie-black-adam-appearance/|title=Shazam! Does Feature THAT Cameo After All (Well, Sort of)|date=April 5, 2019|website=CBR}}</ref> Johnson will portray the titular role in ''[[DC Extended Universe#Black Adam (2021)|Black Adam]]''.\n\nThe [[Seven Deadly Enemies of Man|Seven Deadly Sins]] \u2013 a supernatural team of villains consisting of the demons [[Pride]], [[Envy]], [[Greed]], [[Lust]], [[Wrath]], [[Gluttony]], and [[Sloth (deadly sin)|Sloth]] \u2013 were portrayed by stunt doubles in [[motion capture]] suits on-set during filming, and depicted on-screen through [[computer generated imagery|CGI]] special effects.<ref name=\"TotalFilmShazam\">{{cite magazine |last=Graham |first=Jamie |date=January 2019 |title=Super Size Me |url-access=subscription | url=https://www.myfavouritemagazines.co.uk/film/total-film-magazine-back-issues/total-film-january-2019-issue-281/ |magazine=[[Total Film]] |location=pp. 52-61 |publisher=Future Publishing Ltd. |access-date= }}</ref> Their voices were collectively provided by actors [[Steve Blum]], [[Darin De Paul]], and [[Fred Tatasciore]]. In an [[Easter egg (media)|Easter egg]] [[cameo appearance|appearance]], [[Andi Osho]] reprises her role as social worker Emma Glover from Sandberg's film ''[[Lights Out (2016 film)|Lights Out]]''.<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.cbr.com/shazam-lights-out-share-same-cinematic-universe/ |title= 'Shazam!' & Horror Flick 'Lights Out' Share Same Cinematic Universe, Apparently |website= cbr.com |language= en-US |access-date= 2018-12-07 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20180617165139/https://www.cbr.com/shazam-lights-out-share-same-cinematic-universe/ |archive-date= June 17, 2018 |url-status=live |df= mdy-all }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.andiosho.co.uk/credits/ |title=Credits {{!}} Andi Osho |language=en-US |access-date= 2018-11-02}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author=4 |url=https://www.reddit.com/r/DC_Cinematic/comments/b9o0b4/discussion_was_shazam_not_set_to_feature_a/ek6usiv/ |title=DISCUSSION: Was \"Shazam!\" not set to feature a character from \"Lights Out\" in an Easter Egg Cameo Appearance? : DC_Cinematic |publisher=Reddit.com |date= |accessdate=2019-04-05}}</ref>\n\n==Production==\n===Development===\n[[New Line Cinema]] began development of a ''Shazam!'' live-action feature film in the early 2000s, with multiple screenplay drafts, by [[William Goldman]], the team of [[Alec Sokolow]] and [[Joel Cohen (writer)|Joel Cohen]], Bryan Goluboff, and [[John August]]. The version of the ''Shazam!'' script written by August, which went into pre-production in 2008, was an action-comedy which focused on the origin story of the hero, then known by his original name of Captain Marvel, and his young alter ego, Billy Batson.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://johnaugust.com/2009/shazam-done |title=Shazam! It ain't happening. |website=johnaugust.com |language=en |access-date=2018-02-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180212005359/https://johnaugust.com/2009/shazam-done |archive-date=February 12, 2018 |url-status=live |df=mdy-all }}</ref> [[Peter Segal]]<ref name=\"LOS\">{{cite web | url=http://www.iesb.net/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=4376&Itemid=99 | title=Exclusive: Peter Segal's Shazam Gets a New Title! | work=IESB.net | date=February 23, 2008 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080229074644/http://www.iesb.net/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=4376&Itemid=99 | archive-date=February 29, 2008 | accessdate=December 21, 2017 | url-status=dead | df=mdy-all }}</ref> was attached as director and [[Dwayne Johnson]] was in talks to appear as the film's villain, [[Black Adam]].<ref name=\"LOS\" /><ref name=\"JAugustShazamDone\" /> New Line Cinema was absorbed into [[Warner Bros.]] during the course of development.\n\nFollowing the success of Warner's [[Batman]] film ''[[The Dark Knight (film)|The Dark Knight]]'' and the commercial failure of its lighter, family-friendly ''[[Speed Racer (film)|Speed Racer]]'', both during the summer of 2008, August departed from the project, citing pressure from the studio to make the screenplay darker and more serious.<ref name=\"JAugustShazamDone\">{{cite web |url=https://johnaugust.com/2009/shazam-done |title=Shazam! It ain't happening. |last=August |first=John |website=johnaugust.com |language=en |access-date=2018-07-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180212005359/https://johnaugust.com/2009/shazam-done |archive-date=February 12, 2018 |url-status=live |df=mdy-all }}</ref><ref>{{cite web | last=Seijas | first=Casey | date=January 6, 2009 | url=http://www.mtv.com/news/2593374/shazam-screenwriter-on-film-development-it-wont-be-happening/ | title='Shazam!' Screenwriter On Film Development: 'It Won't Be Happening' | work=MTV News}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | last=Marshall | first=Rick | date=January 13, 2009 | url=http://splashpage.mtv.com/2009/01/13/captain-marvelshazam-movie-still-alive-producer-michael-uslan-hints-at-films-future/ | title=Captain Marvel/Shazam Movie Still Alive? Producer Michael Uslan Hints at Film's Future | work=MTV News | accessdate=January 19, 2008 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110727141249/http://splashpage.mtv.com/2009/01/13/captain-marvelshazam-movie-still-alive-producer-michael-uslan-hints-at-films-future/ | archive-date=July 27, 2011 | url-status=live | df=mdy-all }}</ref> In August 2009, Bill Birch and Geoff Johns, a prominent DC Comics writer, were assigned to write the screenplay, while Segal remained attached as director.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2009/film/markets-festivals/bill-birch-to-write-shazam-reboot-1118007487/|work=Variety|title=Bill Birch to write \u2018Shazam!\u2019 reboot|first=Dave|last=McNary|date=August 19, 2009}}</ref> In August 2010, the studio considered canceling the theatrical movie in favor of a live-action series for prime time network television.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://latimesblogs.latimes.com/herocomplex/2010/08/captain-marvel-dc-shazam.html | work=[[Los Angeles Times]] | title=Captain Marvel Takes Flight But Will He Ever Reach the Big Screen | first=Geoff | last=Boucher | access-date=August 20, 2014 | archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6GG0TPXkM?url=http://herocomplex.latimes.com/movies/captain-marvel-dc-shazam/ | archive-date=April 30, 2013 | url-status=live | df=mdy-all | date=2010-08-06 }}</ref> In December 2013, Segal stated that the film would not be happening, as the similarities between Captain Marvel and [[Superman]] had become an obstacle after the successful launch of ''[[Man of Steel (film)|Man of Steel]]'' earlier that year.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.comingsoon.net/news/movienews.php?id=112833|title=Interview: Director Peter Segal Steps Into the Ring for Grudge Match - ComingSoon.net|date=December 23, 2013|publisher=|access-date=August 20, 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140705042214/http://www.comingsoon.net/news/movienews.php?id=112833|archive-date=July 5, 2014|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nWhile development on the ''Shazam!'' film was in limbo, DC Comics rebooted the comic book franchise as part of their [[The New 52|New 52]] relaunch in 2012. Due to ongoing trademark conflicts with [[Marvel Comics]], who owned the trademark for \"Captain Marvel\" for use with [[Captain Marvel (Marvel Comics)|their own character of the same name]],<ref name=\"NRLostYearsPt3\">{{cite web | url=http://www.newsarama.com/6759-an-oral-history-of-captain-marvel-the-lost-years-pt-3.html | title=An Oral History of CAPTAIN MARVEL: The Lost Years, pt. 3 | work=Newsarama | date=30 December 2010 | accessdate=11 September 2014 | author=Smith, Zack | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131219044853/http://www.newsarama.com/6759-an-oral-history-of-captain-marvel-the-lost-years-pt-3.html | archive-date=December 19, 2013 | url-status=live | df=mdy-all }}</ref> DC renamed their Captain Marvel superhero character \"Shazam\" at this time.<ref name=\"NameChange\">{{cite web |url=http://www.newsarama.com/comics/geoff-johns-curse-of-shazam-120126.html |title=Exclusive: GEOFF JOHNS Hopes Lightning Strikes SHAZAM! |publisher=Newsarama.com |date=2012-01-26 |accessdate=2015-07-08 |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6FfNF1nlO?url=http://www.newsarama.com/comics/geoff-johns-curse-of-shazam-120126.html |archive-date=April 6, 2013 |url-status=live |df=mdy-all }}</ref> DC had been required to market and promote the character using the trademark ''Shazam!'', since acquiring the publishing rights from [[Fawcett Comics]] in 1972.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Bricken|first1=Rob|title=The Captain Marvel/Ms. Marvel/Shazam Clusterf*ck Explained|url=https://io9.gizmodo.com/the-captain-marvel-ms-marvel-shazam-clusterf-ck-explai-1251423862|accessdate=5 December 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180131040940/https://io9.gizmodo.com/the-captain-marvel-ms-marvel-shazam-clusterf-ck-explai-1251423862|archive-date=January 31, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Captain Marvel had originated at Fawcett in 1939, but fell into limbo after 1953 following a long legal battle with DC over Captain Marvel's similarities to Superman.<ref name=\"settlement\">{{cite web | url=http://comicbookads.leafpublishing.com/hall-of-covers/whiz99.htm | title=The World's Mightiest Mortal and Big Red Cheese | work=The Museum of Comic Book Advertising | accessdate=2005-06-17 | quote=In 1953, the case was finally settled out of court when Fawcett agreed to quit using the Captain Marvel character(s) and pay DC the sum of $400,000. | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100113052512/http://comicbookads.leafpublishing.com/hall-of-covers/whiz99.htm | archive-date=January 13, 2010 | url-status=live | df=mdy-all }}</ref>\n\nIn April 2014, Warner Bros. revealed their upcoming slate of films based on DC Comics properties. A ''[[Justice League (film)|Justice League]]'' film was set to be released in 2017, alongside adaptations of ''Shazam!'', ''[[Fables (comics)|Fables]]'', and ''[[100 Bullets]]''. The ''Shazam!'' film was tentatively set for release in July 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.scifinow.co.uk/news/justice-league-fables-100-bullets-fables-shazam-films-revealed/|title=Justice League, Fables, 100 Bullets, Metal Men & Shazam Films Revealed|publisher=scifinow.co.uk|date=April 28, 2014|accessdate=April 29, 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140429230156/http://www.scifinow.co.uk/news/justice-league-fables-100-bullets-fables-shazam-films-revealed/|archive-date=April 29, 2014|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://blogs.wsj.com/speakeasy/2014/04/27/warner-bros-details-plans-for-justice-league-movie-exclusive/|title=Warner Bros. Plans 'Justice League' Movie Directed by Zack Snyder (Exclusive)|publisher=blogs.wsj.com|date=April 27, 2014|accessdate=April 29, 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140428223254/http://blogs.wsj.com/speakeasy/2014/04/27/warner-bros-details-plans-for-justice-league-movie-exclusive/?KEYWORDS=Warner+Bros|archive-date=April 28, 2014|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://nikkifinke.com/comic-con/|title=What Warner Bros/DC Comics Is Planning At Comic-Con In July|last=Finke|first=Nikki|work=Nikki Finke|date=June 12, 2014|accessdate=June 12, 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140614070035/http://nikkifinke.com/comic-con/|archive-date=June 14, 2014|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Dwayne Johnson stated he would be starring in ''Shazam!'' that August, but was undecided between portraying Shazam or Black Adam.<ref name=\"ShazamOrAdamforRock\">{{cite magazine|last=McNary|first=Dave|title=Dwayne Johnson Says He\u2019ll Play Role in \u2018Shazam\u2019|url=https://variety.com/2014/film/news/dwayne-johnson-shazam-1201286278/|accessdate=August 20, 2014|magazine=variety.com|date=August 19, 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150709151459/http://variety.com/2014/film/news/dwayne-johnson-shazam-1201286278/|archive-date=July 9, 2015|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> In September, Johnson was cast as Black Adam, while [[Darren Lemke]] was set to write the script.<ref name=\"JohnsonCasted\">{{cite magazine|last=Kroll|first=Justin|title=Dwayne Johnson to Play Black Adam in New Line\u2019s \u2018Shazam,\u2019 Darren Lemke To Script|url=https://variety.com/2014/film/news/dwayne-johnson-to-play-black-adam-in-shazam-darren-lemke-to-script-exclusive-1201294338/|accessdate=September 3, 2014|magazine=variety.com|date=September 3, 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140905071051/http://variety.com/2014/film/news/dwayne-johnson-to-play-black-adam-in-shazam-darren-lemke-to-script-exclusive-1201294338/|archive-date=September 5, 2014|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> In January 2017, Henry Gayden was hired to rewrite Lemke's script.<ref>{{cite magazine|last=Kit|first=Borys|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/dwayne-johnsons-dc-villain-black-adam-getting-his-own-movie-966008|title=Dwayne Johnson's DC Villain Black Adam Getting His Own Movie|date=January 19, 2017|magazine=The Hollywood Reporter|accessdate=January 30, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171206140831/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/dwayne-johnsons-dc-villain-black-adam-getting-his-own-movie-966008|archive-date=December 6, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> In February 2017, [[David F. Sandberg]] was in talks with the studio to direct ''Shazam!'',<ref name=\"SandbergTalks\">{{cite news|last=McNary|first=Dave|title=\u2018Shazam\u2019: Superhero Movie Eyes \u2018Lights Out\u2019 Director|url=https://variety.com/2017/film/news/shazam-movie-lights-out-director-david-sandberg-1201991635/|accessdate=July 25, 2017|work=Variety|date=February 17, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170713123356/http://variety.com/2017/film/news/shazam-movie-lights-out-director-david-sandberg-1201991635/|archive-date=July 13, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> while Dwayne Johnson was set to star in a ''Black Adam'' solo film, as opposed to appearing as the villain in ''Shazam!'',<ref name=\"JohnsonLeaves\">{{cite web|url=https://screenrant.com/dwayne-johnson-no-black-adam-shazam-geoff-johns/|title=Dwayne Johnson Won't Be in Shazam, Confirms Geoff Johns|website=Screenrant|last=Hood|first=Cooper|date=July 21, 2017|access-date=September 20, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170725000644/http://screenrant.com/dwayne-johnson-no-black-adam-shazam-geoff-johns/|archive-date=July 25, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> while [[Doctor Sivana]], another nemesis of Shazam, became the ''Shazam!'' film's main villain.<ref name=\"Strong\">{{cite web|last=Kit|first=Borys|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/shazam-mark-strong-talks-villain-role-1054332|title='Shazam!': Mark Strong in Talks for Villain Role|date=November 2, 2017|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|accessdate=November 2, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171103015217/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/shazam-mark-strong-talks-villain-role-1054332|archive-date=November 3, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nBy July 2017, the studio had begun active development on ''Shazam!'' and Sandberg was confirmed as director, with production to begin in early 2018.<ref name=\"ShazamSpeedUp\">{{cite news|last=Kit|first=Borys|title='Shazam!' Is Next DC Movie to Shoot (Exclusive)|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/shazam-is-next-dc-movie-shoot-1022821|accessdate=July 22, 2017|work=The Hollywood Reporter|date=July 20, 2017|language=en|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170722071311/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/shazam-is-next-dc-movie-shoot-1022821|archive-date=July 22, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Dwayne Johnson relayed that a different creative team was now involved than when he first signed on to the film.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://screenrant.com/dwayne-johnson-black-adam-shazam-movies/|title=The Rock Wishes Shazam Team 'Best of Luck'|last=Leane|first=Rob|website=Screen Rant|date=December 16, 2017|accessdate=December 16, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171208122416/https://screenrant.com/dwayne-johnson-black-adam-shazam-movies/|archive-date=December 8, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> After being cast as the lead, Zachary Levi stated in an interview, \"the idea is that it's gonna feel like the movie ''[[Big (film)|Big]]'', but with [[Superpower (ability)|super powers]],\" when was asked about the direction [[DC Films]] and New Line Cinema are going for with ''Shazam!''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cinemablend.com/news/1838370/zachary-levi-compares-shazam-to-a-classic-tom-hanks-movie|title=Zachary Levi Compares Shazam To A Classic Tom Hanks Movie|last=Holmes|first=Adam|date=January 10, 2018|publisher=CinemaBlend|accessdate=January 10, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180130091322/https://www.cinemablend.com/news/1838370/zachary-levi-compares-shazam-to-a-classic-tom-hanks-movie|archive-date=January 30, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Warner Bros. stated that the film would be based on the 2012-2013 ''Shazam!'' backup feature from the ''[[Justice League]]'' comic book, by writer Geoff Johns and artist [[Gary Frank]], which told a modernized version of Shazam's origin.<ref name=\"Production\">{{cite web |url= https://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20180205006016/en/ |title= Production Starts on New Line Cinema's Magical Super Hero Action Adventure \"Shazam!\" |work=Business Wire |date= February 5, 2018 |accessdate= February 5, 2018 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20180208195750/https://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20180205006016/en/ |archive-date=February 8, 2018 |url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"GeoffJohnsPR\">{{cite web|url=https://www.warnerbros.com/studio/news/geoff-johns-expand-creative-role-becoming-full-time-writerproducer-film-television|title=GEOFF JOHNS TO EXPAND CREATIVE ROLE BECOMING A FULL-TIME WRITER/PRODUCER FOR FILM, TELEVISION AND MORE; EXCLUSIVE TO DC AND WARNER BROS.|work=Warner Bros. Entertainment|date=June 11, 2018|accessdate=June 12, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180614151940/https://www.warnerbros.com/studio/news/geoff-johns-expand-creative-role-becoming-full-time-writerproducer-film-television|archive-date=June 14, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\n===Pre-production===\nIn August 2017, director David F. Sandberg stated that the film would be the next to shoot in the DC universe,<ref name=\"HeroicHollywoodInterview\">{{cite news|last1=Peris|first1=Sebastian|title='Shazam' Director Says Earlier Versions Of The Script Featured Black Adam|url=https://heroichollywood.com/shazam-earlier-script-black-adam/|accessdate=August 17, 2017|publisher=Heroic Hollywood|date=August 16, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170909095302/https://heroichollywood.com/shazam-earlier-script-black-adam/|archive-date=September 9, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> and by the end of the month, it had begun [[Film and television production manager|pre-production]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Auger|first=Andrew|title=Shazam! Has Officially Begun Pre-Production|url=https://screenrant.com/shazam-movie-casting-filming/|accessdate=August 30, 2017|website=Screen Rant|date=August 29, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170902092820/http://screenrant.com/shazam-movie-casting-filming/|archive-date=September 2, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> By October 2017, cinematographer [[Maxime Alexandre]] and production designer Jennifer Spence, who previously worked with Sandberg on ''[[Annabelle: Creation]]'', were added to the production.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://omegaunderground.com/2017/10/19/shazam-adds-annabelle-2-cinematographer-production-designer/|title='Shazam!' Adds 'Annabelle 2' Cinematographer and Production Designer|last=Marc|first=Christopher|date=October 19, 2017|publisher=OmegaUnderground|accessdate=May 21, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180522111745/https://omegaunderground.com/2017/10/19/shazam-adds-annabelle-2-cinematographer-production-designer/|archive-date=May 22, 2018|url-status=dead|df=mdy-all}}</ref> The next month, ''[[Aquaman (film)|Aquaman]]'' stunt coordinator Kyle Gardiner was hired to work on the film's action sequences.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://omegaunderground.com/2017/11/24/shazam-hires-thor-ragnarok-aquaman-stunt-coordinator/|title='Shazam!' Hires 'Thor: Ragnarok' and 'Aquaman' Stunt Coordinator|last=Marc|first=Christopher|date=November 24, 2017|publisher=OmegaUnderground|accessdate=May 21, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180522111809/https://omegaunderground.com/2017/11/24/shazam-hires-thor-ragnarok-aquaman-stunt-coordinator/|archive-date=May 22, 2018|url-status=dead|df=mdy-all}}</ref> On January 12, 2018, the film's release date was announced as April 19, 2019, later moved to April 5.<ref name=\"ShazamDate\">{{cite news|last1=McNary|first1=Dave|title=DC\u2019s \u2018Shazam!\u2019 Gets 2019 Release Date|url=https://variety.com/2018/film/news/shazam-release-date-2019-1202663057/|accessdate=June 18, 2018|work=Variety|date=January 12, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180618152336/https://variety.com/2018/film/news/shazam-release-date-2019-1202663057/|archive-date=June 18, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\n===Casting===\n[[File:Zachary Levi by Gage Skidmore 4.jpg|thumb|upright|Zachary Levi at 2018 [[San Diego Comic-Con International]]]]\nBy September 2014, Dwayne Johnson was set to portray Black Adam in the film, but by July 2017, he had left the project to pursue a Black Adam solo film.<ref name=\"JohnsonCasted\" /><ref name=\"JohnsonLeaves\" /> In August 2017, the casting process for Shazam and other characters had begun. Sandberg had stated in an interview that instead of de-aging an actor using special effects or CGI, he would cast both a child actor and an adult actor for the role of the main character.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://heroichollywood.com/david-sandberg-shazam-annabelle-creation/|title=David Sandberg On Moving Right Into 'Shazam' From 'Annabelle: Creation'|last=Peris|first=Sebastian|date=August 25, 2017|publisher=Heroic Hollywood|accessdate=August 25, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170826072759/https://heroichollywood.com/david-sandberg-shazam-annabelle-creation/|archive-date=August 26, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> [[Zachary Levi]], [[John Cena]], [[Zane Holtz]], [[Jake McDorman]], [[Derek Theler]] and [[Billy Magnussen]] all met with and/or auditioned for Sandberg for the role of Shazam.<ref>{{cite magazine|last=Kit|first=Borys|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/shazam-star-zachary-levi-as-dc-hero-1049616|title=''Shazam!'' To Star Zachary Levi (EXCLUSIVE)|date=October 27, 2017|magazine=The Hollywood Reporter|accessdate=April 26, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180501061933/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/shazam-star-zachary-levi-as-dc-hero-1049616|archive-date=May 1, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nBy October 2017, Levi was cast in the titular role.<ref name=\"THRLevi\">{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/shazam-star-zachary-levi-as-dc-hero-1049616|title=DC's 'Shazam!' to Star Zachary Levi|last=Kit|first=Borys|date=October 27, 2017|publisher=TheHollywoodReporter|accessdate=October 27, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171028011957/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/shazam-star-zachary-levi-as-dc-hero-1049616|archive-date=October 28, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> In November, [[Grace Fulton]] joined the cast as [[Mary Marvel|Mary Bromfield]], one of Billy Batson's foster siblings.<ref>{{cite web |author=Michael Vassallo |url=https://heroichollywood.com/shazam-grace-fulton-mary-marvel/ |title=DC Comic's 'Shazam!' Director Confirms Grace Fulton Is Mary Marvel |publisher=Heroichollywood.com |date=September 1, 2017 |accessdate=December 16, 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171217014153/https://heroichollywood.com/shazam-grace-fulton-mary-marvel/ |archive-date=December 17, 2017 |url-status=live |df=mdy-all }}</ref> Fulton had previously worked with the same director on ''[[Annabelle: Creation]]''.<ref name=\"Fulton\">{{cite web|last=Kroll|first=Justin|url=https://variety.com/2017/film/news/grace-fulton-shazam-annabelle-creation-1202605521/amp/|title=''Annabelle Creation'' Actress Grace Fulton Joins ''Shazam''|date=November 2, 2017|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|accessdate=November 2, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171107011710/http://variety.com/2017/film/news/grace-fulton-shazam-annabelle-creation-1202605521/amp/|archive-date=November 7, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Later that month, [[Mark Strong]] was in final negotiations to play Dr. Sivana.<ref name=\"Strong\"/> Strong confirmed he would be playing the role by January 2018.<ref>{{cite web|last=Sky|first=Rick|url=http://www.contactmusic.net/mark-strong/news/mark-strong-spills-on-shazam-secrecy_5955962|title=Mark Strong spills on Shazam! secrecy|date=January 14, 2018|publisher=ContactMusic.net|accessdate=January 14, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180115001725/http://www.contactmusic.net/mark-strong/news/mark-strong-spills-on-shazam-secrecy_5955962|archive-date=January 15, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> By November 2017, [[Asher Angel]] was cast as the titular hero's teenage originator [[Billy Batson]].<ref name=\"auto\">{{cite magazine|last=Kit|first=Borys|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/shazam-asher-angel-star-as-billy-batson-dc-movie-1055189|title='Shazam!' Finds Its Billy Batson with 'Andi Mack' Actor|date=November 6, 2017|magazine=The Hollywood Reporter|accessdate=November 6, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171107070958/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/shazam-asher-angel-star-as-billy-batson-dc-movie-1055189|archive-date=November 7, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> In December, [[Jack Dylan Grazer]] was added as [[Captain Marvel Jr.|Freddy Freeman]], Batson's best friend.<ref name=\"Grazer\">{{cite magazine|last=N'Duka|first=Amanda|url=https://deadline.com/2017/12/it-jack-dylan-grazer-shazam-dc-movie-1202221613/|title=''It'' Actor Jack Dylan Grazer Joins ''Shazam''|date=December 6, 2017|magazine=Deadline|accessdate=December 6, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171207013228/http://deadline.com/2017/12/it-jack-dylan-grazer-shazam-dc-movie-1202221613/|archive-date=December 7, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Later that month, Jovan Armand, [[Ian Chen (actor)|Ian Chen]], Faithe Herman, and [[Cooper Andrews]] were cast as [[Marvel Family#Pedro|Pedro Pe\u00f1a]], [[Marvel Family#Eugene|Eugene Choi]], and [[Marvel Family#Darla|Darla Dudley]], with Andrews portraying Victor Vazquez, one of Billy Batson's foster parents.<ref name=\"Herman\">{{cite web|last=Outlaw|first=Kofi|url=https://comicbook.com/dc/2017/12/21/dc-shazam-movie-faithe-herman-darla-dudley/|title=DC's 'Shazam' Adds 'This Is Us' Actress Faithe Herman to Cast|date=December 21, 2017|publisher=Comicbook|accessdate=December 21, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171222091426/http://comicbook.com/dc/2017/12/21/dc-shazam-movie-faithe-herman-darla-dudley/|archive-date=December 22, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"ChenArmand\"/><ref name=\"Andrews\">{{cite magazine|last=N'Duka|first=Amanda|url=https://deadline.com/2017/12/the-walking-deads-cooper-andrews-shazam-new-line-1202229944/|title=''The Walking Dead's'' Cooper Andrews Joins ''Shazam''|date=December 19, 2017|magazine=Deadline|accessdate=December 19, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171221000304/http://deadline.com/2017/12/the-walking-deads-cooper-andrews-shazam-new-line-1202229944/|archive-date=December 21, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nBy January 2018, [[Ron Cephas Jones]] entered talks to play the role of the wizard [[Shazam (wizard)|Shazam]], who granted Batson his powers.<ref name=\"Jones\">{{cite web|last=Gonzalez|first=Umberto|url=https://www.thewrap.com/ron-cephas-jones-wizard-dc-superhero-shazam/|title='This Is Us' Star Ron Cephas Jones Circles Wizard Role in DC Superhero Film 'SHAZAM!' (Exclusive)|date=January 18, 2018|website=TheWrap|accessdate=January 18, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180119003130/https://www.thewrap.com/ron-cephas-jones-wizard-dc-superhero-shazam/|archive-date=January 19, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Later that month, Spanish actress Marta Milans joined the cast to play Rosa Vazquez, one of the foster parents at the home where Billy lives.<ref name=\"Milans\">{{cite magazine|last=Ramos|first=Dino-Ray|url=https://deadline.com/2018/01/shazam-marta-milans-zachary-levi-new-line-comic-book-superhero-film-1202266511/|title='Shazam!': Marta Milans Joins Zachary Levi In New Line Superhero Pic|date=January 22, 2018|magazine=Deadline|accessdate=January 22, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180123052819/http://deadline.com/2018/01/shazam-marta-milans-zachary-levi-new-line-comic-book-superhero-film-1202266511/|archive-date=January 23, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> By the end of January 2018, actress [[Lotta Losten]], the wife of director David F. Sandberg, revealed that she has a role in the film.<ref name=\"Losten\">{{cite tweet|user=lottalosten|last=Losten|first=Lotta|number=958799702094438406|title=Yes! I have a role in Shazam! I can finally say that!|date=January 31, 2018|accessdate=January 31, 2017}}</ref> On April 23, 2018, [[Ross Butler (actor)|Ross Butler]] was announced to have joined the cast.<ref name=\"Butler\">{{cite web|last=Kroll|first=Justin|url=https://variety.com/2018/film/news/riverdale-and-13-reasons-why-ross-butler-shazam-1202783587/|title='13 Reasons Why' Actor Ross Butler Joins DC's 'Shazam!'|date=April 23, 2018|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|accessdate=April 23, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180424112013/http://variety.com/2018/film/news/riverdale-and-13-reasons-why-ross-butler-shazam-1202783587/|archive-date=April 24, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> By July, [[Djimon Hounsou]] had replaced Jones as the wizard Shazam, due to Jones having scheduling conflicts.<ref name=\"Hounsou\">{{cite web |url=https://ew.com/movies/2018/07/10/djimon-hounsou-shazam-wizard |title=Exclusive: DC's 'Shazam!' casts 'Guardians' actor Djimon Hounsou as the Wizard |website=EW.com |language=en |access-date=2018-07-10 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180710194534/http://ew.com/movies/2018/07/10/djimon-hounsou-shazam-wizard/ |archive-date=July 10, 2018 |url-status=live |df=mdy-all }}</ref> [[Henry Cavill]] was in talks to reprise his role as [[Superman]] from previous DCEU films for a [[Cameo appearance|cameo]], but was unable to because of scheduling.<ref>{{cite web|first1=Tatiana|last1=Siegel|first2=Borys|last2=Kit|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/henry-cavill-as-superman-warner-bros-dc-universe-shake-up-1142306|title=Henry Cavill Out as Superman Amid Warner Bros.' DC Universe Shake-Up (Exclusive)|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=12 September 2018|accessdate=12 September 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180912191747/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/henry-cavill-as-superman-warner-bros-dc-universe-shake-up-1142306|archive-date=September 12, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\n===Filming===\nPrincipal photography for ''Shazam!'' began in [[Toronto]] and [[Hamilton, Ontario|Hamilton]], in Ontario, Canada on January 29, 2018, under the [[working title]] ''Franklin'',<ref>{{cite news|last=Mitchell|first=Bea|title=Superhero movie Shazam! to start filming in early 2018|url=http://www.digitalspy.com/movies/shazam/news/a838482/shazam-movie-2019-release-date-dceu-filming-2018/|accessdate=September 20, 2017|work=DigitalSpy|date=September 19, 2017|language=en|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170921174657/http://www.digitalspy.com/movies/shazam/news/a838482/shazam-movie-2019-release-date-dceu-filming-2018/|archive-date=September 21, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"FilmingCanada2\">{{cite web |url=http://omegaunderground.com/2017/09/14/working-title-shazam-movie-revealed/ |title=The Working Title of The 'Shazam!' Movie Revealed |last=Marc |first=Christopher |date=2017-09-14 |website=OmegaGround |access-date=2017-09-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170920103858/http://omegaunderground.com/2017/09/14/working-title-shazam-movie-revealed/ |archive-date=September 20, 2017 |url-status=live |df=mdy-all }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=David F. Sandberg on Instagram: Let's go!\u26a1\ufe0f|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/BeipkbDAYpp/|publisher=[[Instagram]]|accessdate=29 January 2018}}</ref> and wrapped by mid-May 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.toronto.ca/business-economy/industry-sector-support/film/current-productions-and-news/|title=Current Productions & News|publisher=Toronto.ca|accessdate=March 6, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180320211154/https://www.toronto.ca/business-economy/industry-sector-support/film/current-productions-and-news/|archive-date=March 20, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all|date=2017-08-07}}</ref> The film was set primarily in [[Philadelphia]], [[Pennsylvania]] and is firmly established within the DCEU.<ref name=\"Production\" /> Most of the production was shot at [[Pinewood Toronto Studios]], and also several public locations around the city, including the [[University of Toronto]], [[Woodbine Centre|Woodbine Shopping Centre]],<ref name=\"FilmingCanada\">{{cite web |url=http://omegaunderground.com/2017/09/18/confirmed-shazam-begins-filming-february-toronto/ |title=CONFIRMED: 'Shazam!' Begins Filming This February in Toronto |last=Williams |first=Caleb |date=2017-09-18 |website=OmegaGround |access-date=2017-09-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170930183308/http://omegaunderground.com/2017/09/18/confirmed-shazam-begins-filming-february-toronto/ |archive-date=September 30, 2017 |url-status=live |df=mdy-all }}</ref> and [[Hearn Generating Station]]. In early March 2018, filming took place at [[Fort York|Fort York National Historic Site]] in downtown Toronto.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cbr.com/shazam-set-video-costume-zachary-levi/|title=Shazam Set Video Shows Zachary Levi's DC Hero In Action|last=Cohen|first=Jason|date=March 6, 2018|publisher=CBR.com|accessdate=March 6, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180307151038/https://www.cbr.com/shazam-set-video-costume-zachary-levi/|archive-date=March 7, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> By early May 2018, Asher Angel, among other young cast members, had finished filming his part,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://screenrant.com/shazam-asher-angel-wraps-filming/|title=Shazam! Star Asher Angel Officially Wraps Filming|last=Hood|first=Cooper|date=May 7, 2018|publisher=ScreenRant.com|accessdate=May 7, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180508052829/https://screenrant.com/shazam-asher-angel-wraps-filming/|archive-date=May 8, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> and principal photography wrapped on May 11, 2018.<ref name=\"ShazamWrapped\">{{cite tweet|user=ponysmasher|last=Sandberg|first=David F.|number=9995017103894695936|title=That\u2019s a wrap on Shazam! Now onto months of post production.|date=May 11, 2018|accessdate=May 11, 2018}}</ref> Additional photography took place in Toronto between November and December 2018.<ref>{{cite web|last=Marc|first=Christopher|url=https://thegww.com/shazam-confirmed-to-get-two-weeks-of-reshoots-next-month-in-toronto/|title=''Shazam!'' Confirmed To Get Two Weeks Of Reshoots Next Month In Toronto|date=October 23, 2018|work=OmegaUnderground|publisher=Geeks WorldWide|accessdate=October 24, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181025071007/https://thegww.com/shazam-confirmed-to-get-two-weeks-of-reshoots-next-month-in-toronto/|archive-date=October 25, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://screenrant.com/shazam-movie-reshoots-schedule-extended/ |title=Shazam! Reshoots Reportedly Extended To Late December |date=2018-11-08 |website=ScreenRant |language=en-US |access-date=2018-11-10 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181110160107/https://screenrant.com/shazam-movie-reshoots-schedule-extended/ |archive-date=November 10, 2018 |url-status=live |df=mdy-all }}</ref> Scenes set at the [[Philadelphia Museum of Art]], and well as other location work such as footage of the [[skyline]] and [[Aerial photography|aerial shots]], were filmed in the city of [[Philadelphia]] in December 2018.<ref>{{cite web|last=HughE|first=Dillon|url=https://www.phillychitchat.com/2018/11/kendall.html|title='SHAZAM Films in Philly this Weekend, Kendall Jenner will be at Sixers Game Tonight|date=November 30, 2018|work=Philly ChitChat|accessdate=December 2, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181203055443/https://www.phillychitchat.com/2018/11/kendall.html|archive-date=December 3, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> ''Shazam!'' had a production budget of $90\u2013100 million (and about $102 million once post-production was complete), making it the least expensive DCEU film to-date.<ref name=\"Fuster\"/><ref name=preview/><ref>{{cite web|last=D'Alessandro|first=Anthony|url=https://deadline.com/2019/04/shazam-sequel-henry-gayden-screenwriter-returning-1202591584/|title=\u2018Shazam!\u2019 Scribe Henry Gayden To Pen Sequel|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=April 8, 2019|accessdate=April 20, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://screenrant.com/shazam-low-budget-suit-costs/|title=Shazam Budget Reportedly $80-$90M; Suits Didn't Cost $1M|date=2019-01-19|website=ScreenRant|language=en-US|access-date=2019-01-30}}</ref>\n\n===Post-production===\nDavid F. Sandberg's two-time collaborator Michel Aller served as the editor for ''Shazam!''.<ref name=\"Production\" /> Mike Wassel (''[[Hellboy II: The Golden Army]]'' and ''[[The Fast and the Furious]]'' franchise) and Kelvin McIlwain (''[[Aquaman (film)|Aquaman]]'') were the overall visual effects supervisors for the film. [[Technicolor SA|Technicolor]]'s VFX studios Mr. X (known for ''[[The Shape of Water]]'' and ''[[Tron: Legacy]]'') and [[Moving Picture Company]] (MPC) provided [[visual effects]]. [[Rodeo FX]], [[DNEG]], [[Digital Domain]], and [[Rise FX]] also worked on the VFX.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.artofvfx.com/shazam/|title=Art of VFX Shazam!|work=Art of VFX|date=January 21, 2019|accessdate=January 21, 2019}}</ref>\n\nMr. X was responsible for the scenes inside the Rock of Eternity, a dark cave-like environment where the Seven Deadly Sins are imprisoned. Four major sequences take place here, including the opening scene when a young Thad enters and is rejected as the new hero; when he returns as the older Dr. Sivana; when Billy enters and becomes Shazam; and the final showdown between Shazam and Sivana. VFX Supervisor Aaron Weintraub and the team at Mr. X were brought on board three months before shooting began in Toronto \u2013 where the town was abuzz with this exciting project and the mayor talked it up frequently. Weintraub found working with Sandberg and the filmmaking team to be an open, inviting, and collaborative experience.\n\nWhile the first level of the Rock of Eternity was an elaborately built set, everything above 20 feet was a digital environment extension, and within that was every type of visual effect \u2013 from bringing Shazam's chest bolt to life; to stunts with digi-doubles, people melting and statues crumbling; to the Orb and the Seven Deadly Sins flying in and out of it. the final showdown between Shazam and Sivana, in which the latter lets loose his gang of monsters, a 360 shot where seven creatures form from smoke unleashed from within.\n\nRodeo FX team deliver more than 130 shots to DC's latest entry, Shazam!. RodeoFX team recreate the city backdrop for the boardroom sequence. Using photographs of Pittsburgh, They built matte paintings of the city as seen from the boardroom, adding buildings and bustlings streets.\n\nFor the title sequence, They delivered the compositing of the company logos in the opening credits and built and animated the magic 8 ball in CG, adding frost and rays of light beam along matching the effects from the key subway scene from the film.\n\nDigital Domain worked on 26 VFX shots for the movie. Additionally Rise FX and DNEG provide visual effects for the film and the 3D conversion.\n\n==Music==\n{{main|Shazam! (soundtrack)}}\nOn July 21, 2018, [[Benjamin Wallfisch]] was announced as the composer for ''Shazam!'', marking his third collaboration with director David F. Sandberg after previously scoring Sandberg's ''[[Lights Out (2016 film)|Lights Out]]'' and ''[[Annabelle: Creation]]''.<ref>{{cite web |title=Benjamin Wallfisch to Score David F. Sandberg's 'Shazam!' |url=http://filmmusicreporter.com/2018/07/21/benjamin-wallfisch-to-score-david-f-sandbergs-shazam/ |publisher=Film Music Reporter |accessdate=July 21, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180722011452/http://filmmusicreporter.com/2018/07/21/benjamin-wallfisch-to-score-david-f-sandbergs-shazam/ |archive-date=July 22, 2018 |url-status=live |df=mdy-all }}</ref> Wallfisch had also provided additional music for ''[[Batman v Superman: Dawn of Justice]]'', the second film in the [[DC Extended Universe]].<ref>{{cite web |title='BATMAN V SUPERMAN: DAWN OF JUSTICE' - ORIGINAL MOTION PICTURE SOUNDTRACK RELEASE |url=https://www.benjaminwallfisch.com/news/behind-the-scenes-of-the-score-for-the-new-batman-v-superman-dawn-of-justice-movie/ |publisher=Benjaminwallfisch.com |accessdate=August 26, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180827075318/https://www.benjaminwallfisch.com/news/behind-the-scenes-of-the-score-for-the-new-batman-v-superman-dawn-of-justice-movie/ |archive-date=August 27, 2018 |url-status=live |df=mdy-all }}</ref>\n\nWallfisch cited [[John Williams]] and scores from 1980s [[Amblin Entertainment]] films as inspirations for ''Shazam!'', to match the tone of a film about \"an old-school superhero from the [[Golden Age of Comic Books|Golden Age]].\"<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://variety.com/2019/music/news/benjamin-wallfisch-composer-interview-1203181069/ |title=Composer Benjamin Wallfisch Scores High in Versatility With \u2018Hellboy,\u2019 \u2018Hostile,\u2019 \u2018Shazam!\u2019 |last=Burlingame |first=Jon |last2=Burlingame |first2=Jon |date=2019-04-04 |website=Variety |language=en |access-date=2019-04-22}}</ref> In writing the score, Wallfisch stated that he was \"picturing what might happen if a 14-year-old was put in front of a 100 piece orchestra and told there were no limits. I wanted the score to feel like it might have been written by an exuberant kid just having the time of his life with an orchestra.\"<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.dccomics.com/blog/2019/04/19/benjamin-wallfisch-sets-shazams-magic-to-music |title=Benjamin Wallfisch Sets Shazam!'s Magic to Music |last=Beedle |first=Tim |website=DCComics.com}}</ref>\n\n==Marketing==\n[[File:Zachary Levi, Asher Angel, Jack Dylan Grazer & David F. Sandberg by Gage Skidmore.jpg|thumb|(L:R) [[Zachary Levi]], [[Asher Angel]], [[Jack Dylan Grazer]] and [[David F. Sandberg]] promoting ''Shazam!'' at the 2018 [[San Diego Comic-Con|San Diego Comic Con International]]]]\n\nIn April 2018, a first look at ''Shazam!'' was shown at the [[ShoWest Convention|CinemaCon]] convention in [[Las Vegas]], [[Nevada]], as director David F. Sandberg introduced behind-the-scene footage.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Lang|first1=Brent|title=\u2018Aquaman\u2019 Footage Debuts at CinemaCon; \u2018Wonder Woman 2\u2019 Details Revealed|url=https://variety.com/2018/film/news/aquaman-footage-cinemacon-wonder-woman-2-1202785916/|accessdate=April 25, 2018|work=Variety|date=April 24, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180425022253/http://variety.com/2018/film/news/aquaman-footage-cinemacon-wonder-woman-2-1202785916/|archive-date=April 25, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Burlingame|first1=Russ|title=\u2018Shazam!\u2019 Footage Shown at CinemaCon|url=https://comicbook.com/dc/2018/04/25/shazam-footage-shown-at-cinemacon/|accessdate=April 25, 2018|work=Comicbook.com|date=April 24, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180426024009/http://comicbook.com/dc/2018/04/25/shazam-footage-shown-at-cinemacon/|archive-date=April 26, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> During an interview with [[Ryan Connolly (presenter)#Film Riot Mondays|Film Riot Podcast]] in June 2018, Sandberg stated that \"On this one, it was just like 'Yeah, I want this to be a classic superhero movie.' It takes place in the winter, so it's a lot of dark exteriors, but with a lot of colorful lights and stuff around them.\"<ref>{{cite web|last1=Williams|first1=Tommy|title=SHAZAM! Officially Confirmed to Take Place in Winter|url=https://geektyrant.com/news/shazam-officially-confirmed-to-take-place-in-winter|publisher=Geek Tyrant|accessdate=16 June 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180616153839/https://geektyrant.com/news/shazam-officially-confirmed-to-take-place-in-winter|archive-date=June 16, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> On July 21, 2018, the first teaser trailer was shown at [[San Diego Comic-Con]] during the Warner Bros. panel at Hall H, with Sandberg, Zachary Levi, Asher Angel, and Jack Dylan Grazer in attendance. The trailer was later released online.<ref name=\"ComicCon\">{{cite web |last1=Liptak |first1=Andrew |title=The first trailer for DC's Shazam is like Big, but with superheroes |url=https://www.theverge.com/2018/7/21/17598148/shazam-dc-comics-warner-bros-trailer-watch-san-diego-comic-con |website=theverge.com |accessdate=22 July 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180722105234/https://www.theverge.com/2018/7/21/17598148/shazam-dc-comics-warner-bros-trailer-watch-san-diego-comic-con |archive-date=July 22, 2018 |url-status=live |df=mdy-all |date=2018-07-21 }}</ref> It received a favorable response from journalists and audiences, who praised its humorous, zany tone.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Newby |first1=Richard |title=Why 'Shazam!' Was Biggest Surprise of Comic-Con |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/why-shazam-trailer-was-biggest-surprise-comic-con-1129342 |website=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |accessdate=August 13, 2018 |date=July 23, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180814001637/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/why-shazam-trailer-was-biggest-surprise-comic-con-1129342 |archive-date=August 14, 2018 |url-status=live |df=mdy-all }}</ref>\n\nNew footage from the film made its debut at [[Comic Con Experience|Brazil Comic Con]] (CCXP) in [[S\u00e3o Paulo]] on December 9, 2018 during the Warner Bros. studio panel, with the footage described for the attendees as action-packed.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Barnhardt |first1=Adam |title=New 'Shazam!' Footage Debuts at CCXP |url=https://comicbook.com/dc/2018/12/09/new-shazam-footage-ccxp/ |website=Comicbook.com |accessdate=January 4, 2019 |date=December 9, 2018}}</ref> A new trailer was released on March 4, and a three-minute sneak peek was included with the digital home media of ''[[Aquaman (film)|Aquaman]]''. At the [[STP 500]] on March 24, 2019, ''Shazam!'' was the primary sponsor of [[Aric Almirola]] and the #10 [[Ford Mustang]] in the [[Monster Energy NASCAR Cup Series]]. Almirola would go on to finish 9th after starting 2nd.<ref>{{cite web |title=Race Results|url=https://www.nascar.com/results/race_center/2019/monster-energy-nascar-cup-series/stp-500/stn/race/ |website=NASCAR.com |accessdate=March 24, 2019 |date=March 24, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Aric Almirola, a self described Batman fan, to drive Shazam car at Martinsville|url=http://tireball.com/nascar/2019/03/21/aric-almirola-a-self-described-batman-fan-to-drive-shazam-car-at-martinsville/ |website=Tireball.com |accessdate=March 24, 2019 |date=March 21, 2019}}</ref> Altogether the studio spent about $105 million promoting the film.<ref name=DeadlineProfit/>\n\n==Release==\n===Theatrical===\nOn March 13, 2019, [[Warner Bros. Pictures]] announced that they were teaming up with [[Fandango (company)|Fandango]] for exclusive preview screenings on March 23, two weeks before release, on 1,200 select screens and 40 exhibition circuits.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/03/shazam-fandango-early-preview-1202574896/|title=\u2018Shazam!\u2019 To Preview Two Weeks Before Opening Via Fandango Screening Program|author=Anthony D'Alessandro|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=March 13, 2019|accessdate=March 14, 2019}}</ref> ''Shazam!'' premiered in [[Toronto]] on March 15, 2019,<ref>{{cite news |title='Shazam' Toronto Premiere |url=https://etcanada.com/video/1459111491587/shazam-toronto-premiere/ |newspaper=[[Entertainment Tonight Canada]] |date=March 15, 2019 |accessdate=March 24, 2019}}</ref> and was theatrically released in the United States by [[Warner Bros. Pictures]] in [[RealD 3D]], [[Dolby Cinema]], [[4DX]], [[IMAX]], [[ScreenX]] and [[IMAX 3D]] Formats, in April 5, 2019.<ref name=\"ShazamDate\" />\n\n===Home media===\n''Shazam!'' was released on [[Digital distribution|digital download]] on July 2, 2019, and was released on [[Ultra HD Blu-ray]], [[Blu-ray]], and [[DVD]] on July 16. The digital and Blu-ray releases include behind-the-scenes featurettes, deleted scenes, and gag reels.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.slashfilm.com/shazam-blu-ray/|title=\u2018Shazam\u2019 Blu-ray and Digital Releases Arrive in July|date=2019-05-23|website=Slashfilm|language=en-US|access-date=2019-06-19}}</ref> The film was released on home medis in the United Kingdom on August 12, 2019/ also receive a release on Ultra HD Blu-ray, Blu-ray, and DVD on 12 August 2019, in the United Kingdom.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://shop.warnerbros.co.uk/shazam-blu-ray |title=Shazam! (Blu-ray) |website=shop.warnerbros.co.uk |language=en |access-date=2020-04-19}}</ref> {{asof|2020|4|10|df=US}}, ''Shazam!'' has made $8 million in DVD sales and $20.4 million in [[Blu-ray]] sales, totaling an estimated of $28.3 million in domestic video sales.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.the-numbers.com/movie/Shazam-(2019)#tab=summary |title=Shazam! (2019) |website=[[The Numbers (website)|The Numbers]] |accessdate=October 2, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n==Reception==\n===Box office===\n''Shazam!'' grossed $140.4 million in the United States and Canada, and $225.6 million in other territories, for a worldwide total of $366 million.<ref name=BOM/> It was estimated that the film needed to gross $235\u2013250 million worldwide in order to break even,<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/markhughes/2019/04/21/shazam-flies-high-to-300-million-worldwide/#2b51cb8a2ffd|title=\u2018Shazam' Flies High To $300+ Million Worldwide (Updated)|website=[[Forbes]]|author=Mark Hughes|date=April 21, 2019|accessdate=June 27, 2019}}</ref> and ''[[Deadline Hollywood]]'' calculated the film made a net profit of $74&nbsp;million, when factoring together all expenses and revenues.<ref name=DeadlineProfit>{{cite web|url= https://deadline.com/2020/04/shazam-box-office-profit-2019-zachary-levi-dc-comics-1202905779/ |title= \u2018Shazam!\u2019 Hits Grand Slam As No. 21 On Deadline\u2019s 2019 Most Valuable Blockbuster Tournament |first=Anthony|last=D'Alessandro|work=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=April 10, 2019|accessdate=April 10, 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn the United States and Canada, ''Shazam!'' was released alongside ''[[The Best of Enemies (2019 film)|The Best of Enemies]]'' and ''[[Pet Sematary (2019 film)|Pet Sematary]]'', and was projected to gross $40\u201350 million from 4,260 theaters in its opening weekend.<ref name=preview>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/03/shazam-pet-sematary-projected-box-office-opening-1202575628/|title=\u2018Shazam!\u2019 Looks To Strike Lightning With $45M Opening; \u2018Pet Sematary\u2019 Eyes Mid $20M+ \u2013 Early Tracking|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|author=Anthony D'Alessandro|date=March 14, 2019|accessdate=March 14, 2019}}</ref><ref name=VarietyBO>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2019/film/box-office/shazam-box-office-opening-weekend-pet-sematary-1203177258/|title=Box Office: \u2018Shazam!\u2019 Heads Toward $45 Million-Plus Opening Weekend|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|author=Rebecca Rubin|date=April 3, 2019|accessdate=April 3, 2019}}</ref> Two weeks before its release, the film grossed $3.3 million from Fandango advance screenings, higher than the $2.9 million made by fellow DCEU film ''[[Aquaman (film)|Aquaman]]'' the previous December.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/03/shazam-preview-record-box-office-1202581506/|title=\u2018Shazam!\u2019 Paid Previews Are Super At $3.3M, Beating \u2018Dragon 3\u2019, \u2018Aquaman\u2019 & More|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|author=Anthony D'Alessandro|date=March 24, 2019|accessdate=March 24, 2019}}</ref> It then made $5.9 million from Thursday night screenings on April 4, for a combined preview total of $9.2 million.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/04/shazam-pet-sematary-weekend-box-office-opening-1202588955/|title=\u2018Shazam!\u2019 Whams $5.9M In Thursday Night U.S. Previews For $9.2M Cume, Eyes $145M+ WW Launch \u2013 Friday AM Update|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|author=Anthony D'Alessandro|author2=Nancy Tartaglione|date=April 5, 2019|accessdate=April 5, 2019}}</ref> The film grossed a total of $20.5 million on its first day, including Thursday previews but not the March screenings. It went on to debut to $53.5 million, finishing first at the box office.<ref name=opening>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/04/shazam-opening-weekend-box-office-the-joker-pet-sematary-1202589627/|title=\u2018Shazam!\u2019 Shoots To Super $53M+ Opening, $56M+ With Previews; \u2018Pet Sematary\u2019 Purrs $25M \u2013 Sunday AM B.O. Final|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|author=Anthony D'Alessandro|date=April 7, 2019|accessdate=April 7, 2019}}</ref> In its second weekend the film made $25.1 million, retaining the top spot, before being dethroned by newcomer ''[[The Curse of La Llorona]]'' in its third weekend.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/04/hellboy-shazam-weekend-box-office-1202594516/|title=\u2018Shazam!\u2019 Still The Man With $23M+; \u2018Little\u2019 Grows Up; \u2018Hellboy\u2019 Cold With $12M+; \u2018After\u2019 Works Overseas \u2013 Midday B.O. Update|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|author=Anthony D'Alessandro|date=April 14, 2019|accessdate=April 14, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/04/the-curse-of-la-llorona-shazam-easter-weekend-box-office-2-1202598869/|title=Lowest Easter Weekend At The B.O. Since 2005 Despite $26M Purse Of \u2018La Llorona\u2019 \u2013 Saturday AM Update|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|author=Anthony D'Alessandro|date=April 21, 2019|accessdate=April 21, 2019}}</ref> In its fourth weekend, it made $5.8 million and finished fifth at the box office, including behind fellow superhero films ''[[Avengers: Endgame]]'' and ''[[Captain Marvel (film)|Captain Marvel]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/04/avengers-endgame-opening-weekend-box-office-record-1202602445/|title=Avengers: Endgame\u2019 Rests At $357M+ Opening Record; Eyes $33M+ Monday & Record $180M 2nd Frame; Weekend Biz Hits $401M+ High|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|last=D'Alessandro|first=Anthony|date=April 28, 2019|accessdate=April 28, 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn other territories, the film was released in 53 markets on Wednesday, April 3 and Thursday, April 4, and was projected to debut to $100\u2013120 million, for a global opening of $145\u2013170. In its first two days of international release the film made $15.7 million, finishing first in 48 of its 53 markets. It was then released in an additional 26 countries, including China, where it made $16.4 million on its first day. It went on to have an international debut of $102 million, and a global total of $158.6 million. It came in first in 60 of its 79 markets, with its highest-grossing being China ($43.4 million), Mexico ($10.6 million), Australia ($10.3 million), the UK ($15.3 million), Russia ($8.4 million) and Brazil ($8.7 million).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/04/shazam-opening-weekend-china-global-international-box-office-1202589047/|title=\u2018Shazam!\u2019 Strikes $102M Overseas Bow; \u2018Pet Sematary\u2019 Digs $17M; \u2018Dumbo\u2019, \u2018Us\u2019 Top $200M WW \u2013 International Box Office|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|author=Nancy Tartaglione|date=April 7, 2019|accessdate=April 7, 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Critical response===\nAt the [[review aggregator]] website [[Rotten Tomatoes]], the film holds an approval rating of 90% based on 385 reviews, with an [[Weighted arithmetic mean|average rating]] of 7.28/10. The website's critical consensus reads, \"An effortlessly entertaining blend of humor and heart, ''Shazam!'' is a superhero movie that never forgets the genre's real power: joyous wish fulfillment.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/shazam|title=Shazam! (2019)|last=|first=|date=|work=[[Rotten Tomatoes]]|publisher=[[Fandango Media]]|archive-url=|archive-date=|url-status=|accessdate=December 1, 2019}}</ref> On [[Metacritic]], it has a weighted average score of 71 out of 100, based on 53 critics, indicating \"generally favorable reviews.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.metacritic.com/movie/shazam!|title=Shazam! reviews|work=[[Metacritic]]|publisher=[[CBS Interactive]]|accessdate=June 5, 2019}}</ref> Audiences polled by [[CinemaScore]] gave the film an average grade of \"A\" on an A+ to F scale, while those at [[PostTrak]] gave it an overall positive score of 83% and a 61% \"definite recommend.\"<ref name=opening/>\n\nNick Allen of ''[[RogerEbert.com]]'' said that \"while ''Shazam!'' is goofier (and darker) than it may look, you'll wish its superhero came with a little more spark,\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rogerebert.com/reviews/shazam-2019|title=Shazam! Movie Review & Film Summary (2019) {{!}} Roger Ebert|last=Allen|first=Nick|website=www.rogerebert.com|language=en|access-date=2019-04-10}}</ref> while ''[[The Hollywood Reporter]]''{{'}}s Frank Scheck called the film \"''[[Big (film)|Big]]'' on steroids\" and praised the tone and performances.<ref>{{cite web|last=Scheck|first=Frank|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |date=March 23, 2019 |title='Shazam!': Film Review|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/review/shazam-review-1196387}}</ref> [[Alonso Duralde]] of ''[[TheWrap]]'' wrote, \"If the ''Wonder Woman'' and ''Aquaman'' movies represented DC Comics' first big-screen steps away from the austere color palette of the [[Zack Snyder]] movies, ''Shazam!'' takes us deeply into primary colors in a single bound... this new DC entry has a lovely lightness, both in the visuals and in its tone.\"<ref>{{cite web |author-link=Alonso Duralde|last=Duralde|first=Alonso|work=[[TheWrap]] |date=March 23, 2019 |title=\u2018Shazam!\u2019 Film Review: DC Comics Gets a Bouncy Burst of Big-Screen Ebullience|url=https://www.thewrap.com/shazam-film-review-dceu-2019/}}</ref>\n\nWriting for ''[[The A.V. Club]]'', [[Ignatiy Vishnevetsky]] gave the film a \"B\u2212\" and said: \"...while the story of an extremely overpowered champion rising to challenge a one-dimensionally sinister baddie might seem like the epitome of simplicity, ''Shazam!'' is still a modern-day tentpole blockbuster, overburdened with backstories for both hero and villain and subtexts that it can't (or won't) fully articulate.\"<ref name=\"avc\">{{cite web |author-link=Ignatiy Vishnevetsky |last=Vishnevetsky |first=Ignatiy |work=[[The A.V. Club]] |date=March 23, 2019 |title='Shazam!' Zaps an Old-Fashioned Superhero into a Blockbuster World |url=https://film.avclub.com/shazam-zaps-an-old-fashioned-superhero-into-a-blockbus-1833471014}}</ref> That publication followed up with a further consideration of [[masculinity]] in the film and the superhero genre generally, focusing on the transition of Billy Batson from an adolescent boy to a man with power and responsibility.<ref name=\"avcmasc\">{{cite news |url=https://film.avclub.com/shazam-redefines-masculinity-in-the-dc-universe-1833881774 |title=''Shazam!'' Redefines Masculinity in the DC Universe |last=Hassenger |first=Jesse |date=April 9, 2019 |accessdate=April 9, 2019 |newspaper=[[The A.V. Club]]}}</ref> Benjamin Lee of ''[[The Guardian]]'' gave the film 3/5 stars, specifying, \"The finale, while admirably self-contained and small-scale, grinds on for far too long, a boring escalation of anti-climaxes that cumulatively dull the intended emotional impact. It's a film in need of a tighter edit with a script in need of a sharper polish, an imperfect franchise-launcher that nonetheless represents significant progress for DC.\"<ref>{{cite web|last=Lee|first=Benjamin|work=[[The Guardian]] |date=March 23, 2019 |title=Shazam! review \u2013 kid-friendly DC adventure is enjoyably old school |url=https://www.theguardian.com/film/2019/mar/23/shazam-review-zachary-levi-dc-comics-universe}}</ref>\n\n===Accolades===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"width: 99%;\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" | Award\n! scope=\"col\" | Date of ceremony\n! scope=\"col\" | Category\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:35%;\" | Recipients\n! scope=\"col\" | Result\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\" | {{Abbr|Ref.|References}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:center;\"rowspan=\"2\"| [[Golden Trailer Awards]]\n| rowspan=\"2\"| May 29, 2019\n| Best Action\n| ''Shazam!'' \u201cMy Name\u201d, Warner Bros., Buddha Jones\n| {{nom}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"rowspan=\"2\"|<ref>{{cite web |title=Golden Trailer Awards Nominations: \u2018A Star Is Born\u2019, Netflix Lead Way |last=Hipes |first=Patrick |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |date=May 9, 2019 |accessdate=May 15, 2019 |url=https://deadline.com/2019/05/golden-trailer-awards-nominees-2019-nominations-list-netflix-a-star-is-born-1202610742/}}</ref>\n|-\n| Best Action TV Spot\n| ''Shazam!'' \u201cSerious :60\u201d, Warner Bros., Buddha Jones\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:center;\"rowspan=\"2\"| [[MTV Movie & TV Awards]]\n| rowspan=\"2\"|[[2019 MTV Movie & TV Awards|June 17, 2019]]\n| [[MTV Movie Award for Best Comedic Performance|Best Comedic Performance]]\n| rowspan=\"2\"|[[Zachary Levi]]\n| {{nom}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"rowspan=\"2\"|<ref>{{cite web |title=Avengers, Game of Thrones & RBG Lead MTV Movie & TV Awards Nominations |last=Yang |first=Rachel |work=Variety |date=May 14, 2019 |accessdate=May 14, 2019 |url-status=live |url=https://www.variety.com/2019/film/news/avengers-endgame-game-of-thrones-rbg-lead-mtv-movie-tv-award-nominations-1203214680/|archivedate=May 14, 2019 |df=}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[MTV Movie Award for Best Hero|Best Hero]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:center;\"rowspan=\"4\"|[[Saturn Awards]]\n| rowspan=4| [[45th Saturn Awards|September 13, 2019]]\n| [[Saturn Award for Best Comic-to-Film Motion Picture|Best Comic-to-Film Motion Picture]]\n|\n| {{Nominated}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"rowspan=\"4\"|<ref name=\"SaturnReinvigorated\">{{cite web|url=https://www.newsarama.com/46003-saturn-awards-reinvigorated-televised-coming-into-upcoming-45th-anniversary-event.html|title=SATURN AWARDS 'Reinvigorated' & Televised Coming into Upcoming 45th Anniversary Event|website=Newsarama|date=2019-07-12|accessdate=2019-07-28}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=2| [[Saturn Award for Best Performance by a Younger Actor|Best Performance by a Younger Actor]]\n| [[Asher Angel]]\n| {{Nominated}}\n|-\n| [[Jack Dylan Grazer]]\n| {{Nominated}}\n|-\n| [[Saturn Award for Best Costume Design|Best Costume Design]]\n| Leah Butler\n| {{Nominated}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:center;\"rowspan=\"3\"| [[Teen Choice Awards]]\n| rowspan=\"3\"|[[2019 Teen Choice Awards|August 11, 2019]]\n| [[Teen Choice Award for Choice Movie \u2013 Sci-Fi/Fantasy|Choice Sci-Fi/Fantasy Movie]]\n|\n| {{nom}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"rowspan=\"3\"|<ref>{{cite web|title=Hermosa Beach To Host Teen Choice Awards 2019|url=https://patch.com/california/hermosabeach/hermosa-beach-host-teen-choice-awards-2019|first=Emily|last=Holland|work=Patch|date=2019-06-04|accessdate=2019-07-28}}</ref>\n|-\n| Choice Sci-Fi/Fantasy Movie Actor\n| Zachary Levi\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Choice Movie Villain\n| [[Mark Strong]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:center;\"| [[People's Choice Awards]]\n| [[45th People's Choice Awards|November 10, 2019]]\n| Favorite Action Movie of 2019\n|\n| {{nom}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.eonline.com/shows/peoples_choice_awards/news/1068008/2019-people-s-choice-awards-complete-list-of-nominees|title=2019 People's Choice Awards: Complete List of Nominees|date=November 10, 2019|website=E!}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|[[List of awards and nominations received by National Film and Television School|National Film and Television Awards]]\n|December 3, 2019\n|Best Comedy\n|[[David F. Sandberg]]\n|{{won}}\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nationalfilmandtvawards.com/2019/10/nominations-for-the-2nd-annual-national-film-tv-awards-are-announced/|title=Nominations for the 2nd annual National Film & TV Awards are announced|last=Wakeling|first=Naomi|website=National Film & TV Awards|language=en-GB|access-date=2019-12-04}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/B5pEQ99hZQS/|title=David F. Sandberg on Instagram: \u201cJust had one of the weirdest nights of my life...\u201d|website=Instagram|language=en|access-date=2019-12-04}}</ref>\n|-\n|}\n\n==Sequel==\nIn April 2019, ''[[TheWrap]]'' reported that New Line Cinema is developing a sequel with Henry Gayden returning to write the film, along with David F. Sandberg directing and Peter Safran producing.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thewrap.com/henry-gayden-shazam-sequel/|title=\u2018Shazam!\u2019 Writer Henry Gayden Will Return to Write Sequel (Exclusive)|website=The Wrap|last=Gonzalez|first=Umberto|date=April 8, 2019|accessdate=April 8, 2019}}</ref> In December 2019, New Line Cinema announced that the sequel will be released on April 1, 2022.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/12/shazam-2-to-take-flight-spring-2022-sesame-street-relocates-1202807958/|title='Shazam! 2' To Take Flight Spring 2022, 'Sesame Street' Relocates|website=Deadline||last=D'Alessandro|first=Anthony|date=December 12, 2019|accessdate=December 12, 2019}}</ref> But, on April 20, 2020, it was announced that the film would be delayed to November 4, 2022 due to the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]] shifting around the release dates of several films.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2020/04/the-batman-sopranos-prequel-tom-elvis-presley-movie-warner-bros-release-dates-changes-coronavirus-1202912605/|title=\u2018The Batman\u2019 Flies To Fall 2021, \u2018Sopranos\u2019 Prequel Moves To March & More As Warner Bros. Makes Release Date Changes Due To COVID-19 Climate|last=D'Alessandro|first=Anthony|last2=D'Alessandro|first2=Anthony|date=2020-04-20|website=Deadline|language=en|access-date=2020-04-20}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{sisterlinks|display=''Shazam!''|d=Q23685878|c=Category:Shazam! (film)|n=no|b=no|v=no|voy=no|m=no|mw=no|wikt=no|s=no|q=Shazam! (film)|species=no}}\n* {{Official website}}\n* {{IMDb title|0448115}}\n* {{TCMDb title|2170413}}\n\n{{Shazam}}\n{{DC Extended Universe}}\n{{DC Comics films}}\n{{David F. Sandberg}}\n{{Portal bar|Film|United States|Speculative fiction}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Shazam (film)}}\n[[Category:2019 films]]\n[[Category:2019 3D films]]\n[[Category:2010s action films]]\n[[Category:2010s coming-of-age films]]\n[[Category:2010s superhero films]]\n[[Category:American films]]\n[[Category:American action comedy films]]\n[[Category:American action films]]\n[[Category:American adventure comedy films]]\n[[Category:American Christmas films]]\n[[Category:American coming-of-age films]]\n[[Category:American fantasy films]]\n[[Category:American teen comedy films]]\n[[Category:Fantasy action films]]\n[[Category:Captain Marvel (DC Comics) in other media]]\n[[Category:Christmas comedy films]]\n[[Category:DC Extended Universe films]]\n[[Category:English-language films]]\n[[Category:Films about adoption]]\n[[Category:Films about bullying]]\n[[Category:Films about size change]]\n[[Category:Films about wizards]]\n[[Category:Films directed by David F. Sandberg]]\n[[Category:Films produced by Peter Safran]]\n[[Category:Films scored by Benjamin Wallfisch]]\n[[Category:Films set in 1974]]\n[[Category:Films set in the 2000s]]\n[[Category:Films set in 2018]]\n[[Category:Films set in New York (state)]]\n[[Category:Films set in Philadelphia]]\n[[Category:Films set in schools]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Philadelphia]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Toronto]]\n[[Category:Fratricide in fiction]]\n[[Category:Greco-Roman mythology in popular culture]]\n[[Category:IMAX films]]\n[[Category:New Line Cinema films]]\n[[Category:Patricide in fiction]]\n[[Category:Rapid human age change in fiction]]\n[[Category:Rapid human growth change in fiction]]\n[[Category:Films with screenplays by Darren Lemke]]\n[[Category:Seven Bucks Productions films]]\n[[Category:Superhero comedy films]]\n[[Category:Teen superhero films]]\n[[Category:Seven deadly sins in popular culture]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|2019 superhero film directed by David F. Sandberg}}\n{{Use American English|date=August 2019}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=August 2019}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Shazam!\n| image          = Shazam! theatrical poster.jpg\n| border         = yes\n| caption        = Theatrical release poster\n| director       = [[David F. Sandberg]]\n| producer       = [[Peter Safran]]\n| screenplay     = Henry Gayden\n| story          = {{Plainlist|\n* Henry Gayden\n* [[Darren Lemke]]\n}}\n| based on       = {{Based on|[[Captain Marvel (DC Comics)|Captain Marvel]]||[[Bill Parker (comics)|Bill Parker]]|[[C. C. Beck]]}}<!-- Full credit in the film: \"Based on characters from DC Comics\" -->\n| starring       = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Zachary Levi]]\n* [[Mark Strong]]\n* [[Asher Angel]]\n* [[Jack Dylan Grazer]]\n* [[Djimon Hounsou]]\n}}\n| music          = [[Benjamin Wallfisch]]\n| cinematography = [[Maxime Alexandre]]\n| editing        = Michel Aller\n| studio         = {{Plainlist|\n* [[New Line Cinema]]\n* [[DC Films]]\n* [[The Safran Company]]\n}}\n| distributor    = [[Warner Bros. Pictures]]\n| released       = {{Film date|2019|03|15|[[Toronto]]|2019|4|5|United States}}\n| country        = United States\n| language       = English\n| runtime        = 132 minutes<ref name=\"Runtime\">{{cite web|url=https://www.bbfc.co.uk/releases/shazam-2019|title=''Shazam!'' (12A)|publisher=[[British Board of Film Classification]]|accessdate=March 25, 2019}}</ref>\n| budget         = $80\u2013100 million<ref name=\"Fuster\">{{cite web|last=Fuster|first=Jeremy|url=https://www.thewrap.com/shazam-surges-to-53-million-box-office-opening/|title=\u2018Shazam!\u2019 Surges to $53 Million Box Office Opening|website=[[TheWrap]]|date=April 7, 2019|accessdate=April 20, 2019}}</ref><ref name=preview/>\n| gross          = $366 million<ref name=BOM>{{cite web|url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=untitledmovieiv.htm|title=''Shazam!'' (2019)|website=[[Box Office Mojo]]|accessdate=October 25, 2019}}</ref>\n}}\n'''''Shazam! ''''' is a 2019 American [[superhero film]] based on the [[DC Comics]] [[Captain Marvel (DC Comics)|character]]. Produced by [[New Line Cinema]] and distributed by [[Warner Bros. Pictures]], it is the seventh installment in the [[DC Extended Universe]] (DCEU). Directed by [[David F. Sandberg]] from a screenplay by Henry Gayden, and a story by Gayden and [[Darren Lemke]], the film stars [[Asher Angel]] as Billy Batson, a teenage boy who can transform into an adult superhero, played by [[Zachary Levi]]. [[Mark Strong]], [[Jack Dylan Grazer]], [[Adam Brody]], and [[Djimon Hounsou]] also star. The plot follows Billy Batson, who is chosen by the ancient wizard [[Shazam (wizard)|Shazam]] as his new champion and receives various superpowers. Billy and his best friend [[Captain Marvel, Jr.|Freddy Freeman]] (Grazer) must discover Billy's new powers in order to stop the evil [[Doctor Sivana|Dr. Thaddeus Sivana]] (Strong) and the [[Seven Deadly Enemies of Man]].\n\nDevelopment of a live-action ''Shazam!'' film began at New Line in the early 2000s but was delayed for many years. The film went into pre-production in 2009 with director [[Peter Segal]] and writer [[John August]] and [[Dwayne Johnson]] considered to star as the villain [[Black Adam]], but the project fell through; Dwayne Johnson acts as an executive producer on ''Shazam!''. [[William Goldman]], [[Alec Sokolow]], [[Joel Cohen (writer)|Joel Cohen]], Bill Birch, and [[Geoff Johns]], among others, were all attached to the project as writers at various points. The film was officially announced in 2014, with Johnson attached to star as either Shazam or Black Adam. He would later be cast in January 2017 to lead a solo ''Black Adam'' development project, currently targeted for a December 2021 release.<ref name=\"BlackAdamRelease\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/black-adam-release-date-set-2021-1254807 |title=Dwayne Johnson's 'Black Adam' Sets 2021 Release Date |website=The Hollywood Reporter |language=en |access-date=2019-11-19}}</ref> Sandberg signed on to direct ''Shazam!'' in February 2017 and Levi was cast that October, with Angel joining the following month. [[Principal photography]] began in [[Toronto]], [[Ontario]], Canada on January 29, 2018, with most of the film shot at [[Pinewood Toronto Studios]], and [[Wrap (filmmaking)|wrapped]] on May 11, 2018.\n\n''Shazam!'' was released in the United States by [[Warner Bros. Pictures]] in [[RealD 3D]], [[Dolby Cinema]], [[IMAX 3D]], [[4DX]] and [[ScreenX]] <!--no IMAX 2D prints--> on April 5, 2019. The film grossed $366 million worldwide, making it  a box office success. The film received positive reviews from critics, with praise for Sandberg's direction and the performances of Levi, Grazer, and Angel, as well as its light tone and sense of fun.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/shazam-reviews-what-critics-are-saying-1196688|title='Shazam!': What the Critics Are Saying|author=Katie Kilkenny|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=March 23, 2019|accessdate=March 23, 2019}}</ref> A sequel is set for release on November 4, 2022.\n\n==Plot==\n<!-- Per WP:FILMPLOT, the word count in this section should be 400-700 words. -->\nIn 1974 [[Upstate New York]], young [[Doctor Sivana|Thaddeus Sivana]] is riding in a car with his father and brother when he is suddenly transported to the [[Rock of Eternity]], a magical temple in another dimension. There, the ancient wizard [[Shazam (wizard)|Shazam]] has spent centuries searching for someone pure of heart on whom to bestow his power and name as champion, after the previous champion released the [[Seven Deadly Enemies of Man|Seven Deadly Sins]] which killed the rest of the Council of Wizards. Thaddeus is tempted by the Eye of Sin, through which he hears the voices of the Sins, trapped in stone statues, promising him power if he will free them. The wizard deems Thaddeus unworthy and magically returns him to the car, where he makes a scene causing a car crash, crippling his father. The Sins send Thaddeus a message telling him to find them.\n\nIn present-day [[Philadelphia]], 14-year-old foster child [[Captain Marvel (DC Comics)|Billy Batson]] continually runs away from foster homes to search for his birth mother, from whom he became separated while at a carnival ten years prior. He is placed in a group home run by Victor and Rosa Vasquez, with five other foster children: [[Mary Marvel|Mary Bromfield]], Pedro Pe\u00f1a, Eugene Choi, Darla Dudley, and superhero enthusiast [[Captain Marvel Jr.|Freddy Freeman]]. Meanwhile, the embittered Sivana succeeds in his lifelong quest to find a way back to the Rock of Eternity. He steals the Eye of Sin, becoming the Sins' vessel, bests the wizard, and uses his newfound power to kill his father, brother, and Sivana Industries' board of directors.\n\nAt school, Billy defends Freddy from bullies and is chased into a subway, where he is transported to the Rock of Eternity. The wizard chooses Billy to be his new champion: By saying the name \"Shazam\", Billy is transformed into an adult superhero. The wizard turns to dust, leaving his magical staff behind. At home, Freddy is taken into Billy's confidence and helps him explore his newfound powers, which include super strength, speed, near-invulnerability, and electricity manipulation. By saying \"Shazam\" again, he can transform back into his normal body. Freddy posts [[viral video]]s of the new superhero, and Billy starts skipping school to use his powers to [[street performance|busk]] for money and fame, straining his friendship with Freddy. When Billy accidentally endangers and then saves a bus full of people, Sivana confronts him, demanding that he surrender his powers. Billy discovers that he can fly, and manages to escape. His foster siblings deduce that he is the superhero, and complete his search for his mother, who lives nearby. Billy rushes to see her, but is disheartened to learn that she abandoned him, having felt inadequate to raise him as a single teenage mother.\n\nSivana deduces Billy's identity and takes his foster siblings hostage. Billy agrees to transfer his powers to Sivana in exchange for their safety. They go to the Rock of Eternity to use the wizard's staff to effect the transfer, but the children follow and attack Sivana. Billy observes that Sivana becomes vulnerable when all seven Sins leave his body. Sivana pursues them to a winter carnival and unleashes the Sins upon the crowd. Remembering the wizard's words, Billy uses the staff to share his powers with his siblings, transforming them into [[Marvel Family|adult superheroes like him]]. He then breaks the staff, and his siblings battle the Sins while Billy faces down Sivana. By luring out the final Sin, Envy, Billy makes Sivana vulnerable and yanks the Eye of Sin out of his head, recapturing all the Sins.\n\nBilly and his siblings are hailed as heroes, return the Eye and the Sins to their prison, and realize they can use the Rock of Eternity as their superhero lair. Billy finally accepts his foster parents and siblings as his \"real\" family. In his superhero form, he has lunch with his siblings at school, revealing to Freddy's surprise that he has also invited [[Superman]]. In a [[post-credits scene|mid-credits scene]], the imprisoned Sivana is approached by [[Mister Mind|a talking caterpillar]], who proposes [[Monster Society of Evil|an alliance]].\n\n==Cast==\n{{See also|Marvel Family}}\n* [[Asher Angel]] as [[Captain Marvel (DC Comics)|Billy Batson]], a troubled orphan searching for his biological mother, who is chosen by the ancient wizard Shazam as his champion. David Kohlsmith plays the four-year-old Billy.\n** [[Zachary Levi]] as Shazam, the wizard's champion and Billy's superhero alter-ego, who upon saying his name possesses \"the Wisdom of [[Solomon|'''S'''olomon]], the Strength of [[Hercules|'''H'''ercules]], the Stamina of [[Atlas (mythology)|'''A'''tlas]], the Power of [[Zeus|'''Z'''eus]], the Courage of [[Achilles|'''A'''chilles]], and the Speed of [[Mercury (mythology)|'''M'''ercury]]\". Throughout his discoveries of the use of his powers, Billy and Freddy consider using other aliases for the champion, such as \"Captain Sparklefingers\".<ref name=\"Sparklefingers\">{{Cite web |url=https://screenrant.com/shazam-movie-captain-marvel-joke-sparklefists-fingers/|title=Shazam's Trailer Has A Captain Marvel Joke (But You May Have Missed It)|last=Bacon |first=Thomas |website=ScreenRant |language=en |access-date=2020-02-02}}</ref>\n* [[Mark Strong]] as [[Doctor Sivana|Dr. Thaddeus Sivana]], a scientist who was turned down as a potential champion and subsequently estranged from his family, who becomes a host for the [[Seven Deadly Enemies of Man|Seven Deadly Sins]] and Shazam's nemesis. Ethan Pugiotto plays the young Thaddeus.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Ehrlich |first1=David |title='Shazam!' Review: DC Surprises with One of the Most Fun Superhero Movies Ever Made |url=https://www.indiewire.com/2019/03/shazam-movie-review-1202052656/ |work=[[IndieWire]] |date=March 23, 2019 |accessdate=April 4, 2019}}</ref>\n* [[Jack Dylan Grazer]] as [[Captain Marvel Jr.|Frederick \"Freddy\" Freeman]], Billy's physically disabled foster brother and a fan of superheroes, who mentors Billy on the use of his newfound powers. [[Adam Brody]] plays the character's adult superhero form.<ref>{{cite web|last=Hood|first=Cooper|url=https://screenrant.com/shazam-it-jack-dylan-grazer-cast/|title=IT's Jack Dylan Grazer Joins DC's Shazam!|website=ScreenRant|date=December 6, 2017|accessdate=April 20, 2020}}</ref>\n* [[Djimon Hounsou]] as [[Shazam (wizard)|Shazam]], the last surviving member of the Council of Wizards, who has spent centuries summoning people to his temple, the [[Rock of Eternity]], in search of a \"pure of heart\" champion to whom he can pass on his extraordinary faculties.<ref>{{cite web|last=Hibberd|first=James|url=https://ew.com/movies/2018/07/10/djimon-hounsou-shazam-wizard/|title=DC's Shazam! casts Guardians actor Djimon Hounsou as the Wizard|publisher=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|date=July 10, 2018|accessdate=April 20, 2020}}</ref>\n* Faithe Herman as Darla Dudley, Billy's good-natured younger foster sister. [[Meagan Good]] plays the character's adult superhero form.\n* [[Grace Fulton]] as [[Mary Marvel|Mary Bromfield]], Billy's mature, academically-driven older foster sister. [[Michelle Borth]] plays the character's adult superhero form.<ref>{{Cite web| last=Anderson|first=Jenna|url=https://comicbook.com/dc/2018/02/05/shazam-movie-2019-grace-fulton-character-mary-marvel/|title='Shazam!': Grace Fulton Confirmed for Mary Marvel|website=Comic Book.com|date=February 5, 2018|accessdate=April 20, 2020}}</ref>\n* [[Ian Chen (actor)|Ian Chen]] as Eugene Choi, Billy's younger foster brother, an obsessive gamer and techie. [[Ross Butler (actor)|Ross Butler]] plays the character's adult superhero form.<ref name=\"ShazamFamilyActors\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.refinery29.com/en-us/2019/04/228836/who-is-the-superhero-family-in-shazam-brothers-sisters |title=Surprise! Your Fav \"OC\" & \"Riverdale\" Alums Are In \"Shazam\" |last=Bentley |first=Jean |website=www.refinery29.com |language=en |access-date=2019-04-06}}</ref>\n* Jovan Armand as Pedro Pe\u00f1a: Billy's older foster brother, a shy, sensitive boy who has trouble opening up.<ref name=\"ChenArmand\">{{cite magazine|last=N'Duka|first=Amanda|url=https://deadline.com/2017/12/ian-chen-jovan-armand-shazam-brian-astro-bradley-jr-luce-1202225185/amp/|title=Ian Chen & Jovan Armand Join ''Shazam''|date=December 12, 2017|magazine=Deadline|accessdate=December 12, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171213010829/http://deadline.com/2017/12/ian-chen-jovan-armand-shazam-brian-astro-bradley-jr-luce-1202225185/amp/|archive-date=December 13, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> [[D. J. Cotrona]] plays the character's adult superhero form.\n* [[Marta Milans]] as Rosa Vasquez, the foster mother of Billy and his siblings.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Dumaraog|first=Ana|url=https://screenrant.com/shazam-movie-cast-marta-milans/|title=Shazam Casts No Tomorrow's Marta Milans||website=ScreenRant|date=January 23, 2018|accessdate=April 20, 2020}}</ref>\n* [[Cooper Andrews]] as Victor Vasquez, Billy and his siblings\u2019 foster father.<ref>{{cite web|last=Ridgely|first=Charlie|url=https://comicbook.com/dc/2018/02/06/shazam-cooper-andrews-walking-dead-role-revealed/|title='The Walking Dead's Cooper Andrews' 'Shazam!' Role Revealed|website=Comic Book.com|date=February 6, 2018|accessdate=April 20, 2020}}</ref>\n\nThe film also features [[John Glover (actor)|John Glover]] as Mr. Sivana, the estranged father of Dr. Thaddeus Sivana and CEO of Sivana Industries.<ref name=\"JohnGlover\">{{cite web |url=https://www.cbr.com/smallvilles-john-glover-shazam-role/ |title=Smallville's John Glover Reveals His Secret Shazam! Role |date=2019-03-10 |website=CBR |language=en-US |access-date=2019-03-27}}</ref> Glover had previously starred in other DC Comics series and films: ''[[Batman The Animated Series]]''; ''[[The New Batman Adventures]]''; ''[[Superman the Animated Series]]'' as [[The Riddler]]; [[Floronic Man|Dr. Jason Woodrue]] in the 1997 film ''[[Batman & Robin (film)|Batman and Robin]]''; and [[Lionel Luthor]], [[Lex Luthor]]'s father in ''[[Smallville]]''. Natalia Safran was cast as Mrs. Sivana, though her scenes were ultimately cut from the film. Caroline Palmer portrays Marilyn Batson, Billy's biological mother. Wayne Ward and Landon Doak portray Sid the bullying brother of Thaddeus Sivana as an adult and a teenager, respectively. Carson MacCormac and Evan Marsh portray Brett and Burke Breyer, bullies at the children's school.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.memphisflyer.com/NewsBlog/archives/2019/04/01/former-memphian-writes-shazam-screenplay |title=Former Memphian Writes Shazam! Screenplay |last=Donahue |first=Michael |date=2019-04-01 |website=Memphis Flyer |access-date=2019-04-22}}</ref>\n\nDirector [[David F. Sandberg]] makes cameo appearances performing as each of the three Crocodile-Men (collaboratively assisted by Steve Newburn and Ned Morill<!--These two were listed in the credits-->), and provides the voice of the [[Extraterrestrial life|alien lifeform]] [[Mister Mind and the Monster Society of Evil|Mister Mind]] during a mid-credits sequence.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.polygon.com/2019/4/5/18295706/shazam-post-credit-scene-sequel |title=Shazam director reveals the voice behind his post-credits scene tease |last=Patches |first=Matt |date=2019-04-05 |website=Polygon |access-date=2019-04-06}}</ref> Sandberg's wife, actress [[Lotta Losten]], portrays Dr. Lynn Crosby; a researcher working with Dr. Sivana, who is killed by him.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Peris |first1=Sebastian |title='Shazam!' Star Lotta Losten Reveals First Look At Her Character Dr. Lynn Crosby |url=https://heroichollywood.com/shazam-lotta-losten-character-revealed/ |publisher=Heroic Hollywood |date=March 22, 2019 |accessdate=April 4, 2019}}</ref> Sound designer Bill R. Dean has an uncredited cameo, providing the voice for a [[Batman]] toy,<ref>{{cite web |url= https://comicbook.com/dc/2019/03/11/new-batman-toy-voice-actor-in-shazam-revealed/ |title=New Batman Toy Voice Actor In 'Shazam!' Revealed |website= ComicBook.com |language= en-US |access-date= 2019-03-11 |url-status=live |df= mdy-all }}</ref> while Ryan Hadley, Zachary Levi's stunt double, appears uncredited as a stand-in body double for [[Superman]]. Hadley's appearance is a silent cameo, where the character is only seen from the neck down, due to [[Henry Cavill]] being unavailable to film the scene.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2019/04/shazam-david-f-sandberg-director-inclusive-dc-comics-warner-bros-1202588927/ |title=\u2018Shazam!\u2019 Director David F. Sandberg Talks Going Horror To Superhero And Bringing Inclusivity To Family Narrative |last=Ramos |first=Dino-Ray |date=2019-04-05 |website=Deadline Hollywood |access-date=2019-04-06}}</ref> [[Dwayne Johnson]]'s likeness is used for the [[Mysticism|mystic-generated]] [[Holography|holograph]] of [[Black Adam|Teth-Adam]], which the wizard Shazam conjures while teaching Billy the history of the Rock of Eternity, the Seven Realms of Magic, and his previous Champion.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cbr.com/shazam-movie-black-adam-appearance/|title=Shazam! Does Feature THAT Cameo After All (Well, Sort of)|date=April 5, 2019|website=CBR}}</ref> Johnson will portray the titular role in ''[[DC Extended Universe#Black Adam (2021)|Black Adam]]''.\n\nThe [[Seven Deadly Enemies of Man|Seven Deadly Sins]] \u2013 a supernatural team of villains consisting of the demons [[Pride]], [[Envy]], [[Greed]], [[Lust]], [[Wrath]], [[Gluttony]], and [[Sloth (deadly sin)|Sloth]] \u2013 were portrayed by stunt doubles in [[motion capture]] suits on-set during filming, and depicted on-screen through [[computer generated imagery|CGI]] special effects.<ref name=\"TotalFilmShazam\">{{cite magazine |last=Graham |first=Jamie |date=January 2019 |title=Super Size Me |url-access=subscription | url=https://www.myfavouritemagazines.co.uk/film/total-film-magazine-back-issues/total-film-january-2019-issue-281/ |magazine=[[Total Film]] |location=pp. 52-61 |publisher=Future Publishing Ltd. |access-date= }}</ref> Their voices were collectively provided by actors [[Steve Blum]], [[Darin De Paul]], and [[Fred Tatasciore]]. In an [[Easter egg (media)|Easter egg]] [[cameo appearance|appearance]], [[Andi Osho]] reprises her role as social worker Emma Glover from Sandberg's film ''[[Lights Out (2016 film)|Lights Out]]''.<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.cbr.com/shazam-lights-out-share-same-cinematic-universe/ |title= 'Shazam!' & Horror Flick 'Lights Out' Share Same Cinematic Universe, Apparently |website= cbr.com |language= en-US |access-date= 2018-12-07 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20180617165139/https://www.cbr.com/shazam-lights-out-share-same-cinematic-universe/ |archive-date= June 17, 2018 |url-status=live |df= mdy-all }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.andiosho.co.uk/credits/ |title=Credits {{!}} Andi Osho |language=en-US |access-date= 2018-11-02}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author=4 |url=https://www.reddit.com/r/DC_Cinematic/comments/b9o0b4/discussion_was_shazam_not_set_to_feature_a/ek6usiv/ |title=DISCUSSION: Was \"Shazam!\" not set to feature a character from \"Lights Out\" in an Easter Egg Cameo Appearance? : DC_Cinematic |publisher=Reddit.com |date= |accessdate=2019-04-05}}</ref>\n\n==Production==\n===Development===\n[[New Line Cinema]] began development of a ''Shazam!'' live-action feature film in the early 2000s, with multiple screenplay drafts, by [[William Goldman]], the team of [[Alec Sokolow]] and [[Joel Cohen (writer)|Joel Cohen]], Bryan Goluboff, and [[John August]]. The version of the ''Shazam!'' script written by August, which went into pre-production in 2008, was an action-comedy which focused on the origin story of the hero, then known by his original name of Captain Marvel, and his young alter ego, Billy Batson.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://johnaugust.com/2009/shazam-done |title=Shazam! It ain't happening. |website=johnaugust.com |language=en |access-date=2018-02-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180212005359/https://johnaugust.com/2009/shazam-done |archive-date=February 12, 2018 |url-status=live |df=mdy-all }}</ref> [[Peter Segal]]<ref name=\"LOS\">{{cite web | url=http://www.iesb.net/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=4376&Itemid=99 | title=Exclusive: Peter Segal's Shazam Gets a New Title! | work=IESB.net | date=February 23, 2008 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080229074644/http://www.iesb.net/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=4376&Itemid=99 | archive-date=February 29, 2008 | accessdate=December 21, 2017 | url-status=dead | df=mdy-all }}</ref> was attached as director and [[Dwayne Johnson]] was in talks to appear as the film's villain, [[Black Adam]].<ref name=\"LOS\" /><ref name=\"JAugustShazamDone\" /> New Line Cinema was absorbed into [[Warner Bros.]] during the course of development.\n\nFollowing the success of Warner's [[Batman]] film ''[[The Dark Knight (film)|The Dark Knight]]'' and the commercial failure of its lighter, family-friendly ''[[Speed Racer (film)|Speed Racer]]'', both during the summer of 2008, August departed from the project, citing pressure from the studio to make the screenplay darker and more serious.<ref name=\"JAugustShazamDone\">{{cite web |url=https://johnaugust.com/2009/shazam-done |title=Shazam! It ain't happening. |last=August |first=John |website=johnaugust.com |language=en |access-date=2018-07-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180212005359/https://johnaugust.com/2009/shazam-done |archive-date=February 12, 2018 |url-status=live |df=mdy-all }}</ref><ref>{{cite web | last=Seijas | first=Casey | date=January 6, 2009 | url=http://www.mtv.com/news/2593374/shazam-screenwriter-on-film-development-it-wont-be-happening/ | title='Shazam!' Screenwriter On Film Development: 'It Won't Be Happening' | work=MTV News}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | last=Marshall | first=Rick | date=January 13, 2009 | url=http://splashpage.mtv.com/2009/01/13/captain-marvelshazam-movie-still-alive-producer-michael-uslan-hints-at-films-future/ | title=Captain Marvel/Shazam Movie Still Alive? Producer Michael Uslan Hints at Film's Future | work=MTV News | accessdate=January 19, 2008 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110727141249/http://splashpage.mtv.com/2009/01/13/captain-marvelshazam-movie-still-alive-producer-michael-uslan-hints-at-films-future/ | archive-date=July 27, 2011 | url-status=live | df=mdy-all }}</ref> In August 2009, Bill Birch and Geoff Johns, a prominent DC Comics writer, were assigned to write the screenplay, while Segal remained attached as director.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2009/film/markets-festivals/bill-birch-to-write-shazam-reboot-1118007487/|work=Variety|title=Bill Birch to write \u2018Shazam!\u2019 reboot|first=Dave|last=McNary|date=August 19, 2009}}</ref> In August 2010, the studio considered canceling the theatrical movie in favor of a live-action series for prime time network television.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://latimesblogs.latimes.com/herocomplex/2010/08/captain-marvel-dc-shazam.html | work=[[Los Angeles Times]] | title=Captain Marvel Takes Flight But Will He Ever Reach the Big Screen | first=Geoff | last=Boucher | access-date=August 20, 2014 | archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6GG0TPXkM?url=http://herocomplex.latimes.com/movies/captain-marvel-dc-shazam/ | archive-date=April 30, 2013 | url-status=live | df=mdy-all | date=2010-08-06 }}</ref> In December 2013, Segal stated that the film would not be happening, as the similarities between Captain Marvel and [[Superman]] had become an obstacle after the successful launch of ''[[Man of Steel (film)|Man of Steel]]'' earlier that year.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.comingsoon.net/news/movienews.php?id=112833|title=Interview: Director Peter Segal Steps Into the Ring for Grudge Match - ComingSoon.net|date=December 23, 2013|publisher=|access-date=August 20, 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140705042214/http://www.comingsoon.net/news/movienews.php?id=112833|archive-date=July 5, 2014|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nWhile development on the ''Shazam!'' film was in limbo, DC Comics rebooted the comic book franchise as part of their [[The New 52|New 52]] relaunch in 2012. Due to ongoing trademark conflicts with [[Marvel Comics]], who owned the trademark for \"Captain Marvel\" for use with [[Captain Marvel (Marvel Comics)|their own character of the same name]],<ref name=\"NRLostYearsPt3\">{{cite web | url=http://www.newsarama.com/6759-an-oral-history-of-captain-marvel-the-lost-years-pt-3.html | title=An Oral History of CAPTAIN MARVEL: The Lost Years, pt. 3 | work=Newsarama | date=30 December 2010 | accessdate=11 September 2014 | author=Smith, Zack | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131219044853/http://www.newsarama.com/6759-an-oral-history-of-captain-marvel-the-lost-years-pt-3.html | archive-date=December 19, 2013 | url-status=live | df=mdy-all }}</ref> DC renamed their Captain Marvel superhero character \"Shazam\" at this time.<ref name=\"NameChange\">{{cite web |url=http://www.newsarama.com/comics/geoff-johns-curse-of-shazam-120126.html |title=Exclusive: GEOFF JOHNS Hopes Lightning Strikes SHAZAM! |publisher=Newsarama.com |date=2012-01-26 |accessdate=2015-07-08 |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6FfNF1nlO?url=http://www.newsarama.com/comics/geoff-johns-curse-of-shazam-120126.html |archive-date=April 6, 2013 |url-status=live |df=mdy-all }}</ref> DC had been required to market and promote the character using the trademark ''Shazam!'', since acquiring the publishing rights from [[Fawcett Comics]] in 1972.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Bricken|first1=Rob|title=The Captain Marvel/Ms. Marvel/Shazam Clusterf*ck Explained|url=https://io9.gizmodo.com/the-captain-marvel-ms-marvel-shazam-clusterf-ck-explai-1251423862|accessdate=5 December 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180131040940/https://io9.gizmodo.com/the-captain-marvel-ms-marvel-shazam-clusterf-ck-explai-1251423862|archive-date=January 31, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Captain Marvel had originated at Fawcett in 1939, but fell into limbo after 1953 following a long legal battle with DC over Captain Marvel's similarities to Superman.<ref name=\"settlement\">{{cite web | url=http://comicbookads.leafpublishing.com/hall-of-covers/whiz99.htm | title=The World's Mightiest Mortal and Big Red Cheese | work=The Museum of Comic Book Advertising | accessdate=2005-06-17 | quote=In 1953, the case was finally settled out of court when Fawcett agreed to quit using the Captain Marvel character(s) and pay DC the sum of $400,000. | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100113052512/http://comicbookads.leafpublishing.com/hall-of-covers/whiz99.htm | archive-date=January 13, 2010 | url-status=live | df=mdy-all }}</ref>\n\nIn April 2014, Warner Bros. revealed their upcoming slate of films based on DC Comics properties. A ''[[Justice League (film)|Justice League]]'' film was set to be released in 2017, alongside adaptations of ''Shazam!'', ''[[Fables (comics)|Fables]]'', and ''[[100 Bullets]]''. The ''Shazam!'' film was tentatively set for release in July 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.scifinow.co.uk/news/justice-league-fables-100-bullets-fables-shazam-films-revealed/|title=Justice League, Fables, 100 Bullets, Metal Men & Shazam Films Revealed|publisher=scifinow.co.uk|date=April 28, 2014|accessdate=April 29, 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140429230156/http://www.scifinow.co.uk/news/justice-league-fables-100-bullets-fables-shazam-films-revealed/|archive-date=April 29, 2014|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://blogs.wsj.com/speakeasy/2014/04/27/warner-bros-details-plans-for-justice-league-movie-exclusive/|title=Warner Bros. Plans 'Justice League' Movie Directed by Zack Snyder (Exclusive)|publisher=blogs.wsj.com|date=April 27, 2014|accessdate=April 29, 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140428223254/http://blogs.wsj.com/speakeasy/2014/04/27/warner-bros-details-plans-for-justice-league-movie-exclusive/?KEYWORDS=Warner+Bros|archive-date=April 28, 2014|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://nikkifinke.com/comic-con/|title=What Warner Bros/DC Comics Is Planning At Comic-Con In July|last=Finke|first=Nikki|work=Nikki Finke|date=June 12, 2014|accessdate=June 12, 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140614070035/http://nikkifinke.com/comic-con/|archive-date=June 14, 2014|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Dwayne Johnson stated he would be starring in ''Shazam!'' that August, but was undecided between portraying Shazam or Black Adam.<ref name=\"ShazamOrAdamforRock\">{{cite magazine|last=McNary|first=Dave|title=Dwayne Johnson Says He\u2019ll Play Role in \u2018Shazam\u2019|url=https://variety.com/2014/film/news/dwayne-johnson-shazam-1201286278/|accessdate=August 20, 2014|magazine=variety.com|date=August 19, 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150709151459/http://variety.com/2014/film/news/dwayne-johnson-shazam-1201286278/|archive-date=July 9, 2015|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> In September, Johnson was cast as Black Adam, while [[Darren Lemke]] was set to write the script.<ref name=\"JohnsonCasted\">{{cite magazine|last=Kroll|first=Justin|title=Dwayne Johnson to Play Black Adam in New Line\u2019s \u2018Shazam,\u2019 Darren Lemke To Script|url=https://variety.com/2014/film/news/dwayne-johnson-to-play-black-adam-in-shazam-darren-lemke-to-script-exclusive-1201294338/|accessdate=September 3, 2014|magazine=variety.com|date=September 3, 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140905071051/http://variety.com/2014/film/news/dwayne-johnson-to-play-black-adam-in-shazam-darren-lemke-to-script-exclusive-1201294338/|archive-date=September 5, 2014|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> In January 2017, Henry Gayden was hired to rewrite Lemke's script.<ref>{{cite magazine|last=Kit|first=Borys|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/dwayne-johnsons-dc-villain-black-adam-getting-his-own-movie-966008|title=Dwayne Johnson's DC Villain Black Adam Getting His Own Movie|date=January 19, 2017|magazine=The Hollywood Reporter|accessdate=January 30, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171206140831/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/dwayne-johnsons-dc-villain-black-adam-getting-his-own-movie-966008|archive-date=December 6, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> In February 2017, [[David F. Sandberg]] was in talks with the studio to direct ''Shazam!'',<ref name=\"SandbergTalks\">{{cite news|last=McNary|first=Dave|title=\u2018Shazam\u2019: Superhero Movie Eyes \u2018Lights Out\u2019 Director|url=https://variety.com/2017/film/news/shazam-movie-lights-out-director-david-sandberg-1201991635/|accessdate=July 25, 2017|work=Variety|date=February 17, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170713123356/http://variety.com/2017/film/news/shazam-movie-lights-out-director-david-sandberg-1201991635/|archive-date=July 13, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> while Dwayne Johnson was set to star in a ''Black Adam'' solo film, as opposed to appearing as the villain in ''Shazam!'',<ref name=\"JohnsonLeaves\">{{cite web|url=https://screenrant.com/dwayne-johnson-no-black-adam-shazam-geoff-johns/|title=Dwayne Johnson Won't Be in Shazam, Confirms Geoff Johns|website=Screenrant|last=Hood|first=Cooper|date=July 21, 2017|access-date=September 20, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170725000644/http://screenrant.com/dwayne-johnson-no-black-adam-shazam-geoff-johns/|archive-date=July 25, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> while [[Doctor Sivana]], another nemesis of Shazam, became the ''Shazam!'' film's main villain.<ref name=\"Strong\">{{cite web|last=Kit|first=Borys|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/shazam-mark-strong-talks-villain-role-1054332|title='Shazam!': Mark Strong in Talks for Villain Role|date=November 2, 2017|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|accessdate=November 2, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171103015217/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/shazam-mark-strong-talks-villain-role-1054332|archive-date=November 3, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nBy July 2017, the studio had begun active development on ''Shazam!'' and Sandberg was confirmed as director, with production to begin in early 2018.<ref name=\"ShazamSpeedUp\">{{cite news|last=Kit|first=Borys|title='Shazam!' Is Next DC Movie to Shoot (Exclusive)|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/shazam-is-next-dc-movie-shoot-1022821|accessdate=July 22, 2017|work=The Hollywood Reporter|date=July 20, 2017|language=en|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170722071311/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/shazam-is-next-dc-movie-shoot-1022821|archive-date=July 22, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Dwayne Johnson relayed that a different creative team was now involved than when he first signed on to the film.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://screenrant.com/dwayne-johnson-black-adam-shazam-movies/|title=The Rock Wishes Shazam Team 'Best of Luck'|last=Leane|first=Rob|website=Screen Rant|date=December 16, 2017|accessdate=December 16, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171208122416/https://screenrant.com/dwayne-johnson-black-adam-shazam-movies/|archive-date=December 8, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> After being cast as the lead, Zachary Levi stated in an interview, \"the idea is that it's gonna feel like the movie ''[[Big (film)|Big]]'', but with [[Superpower (ability)|super powers]],\" when was asked about the direction [[DC Films]] and New Line Cinema are going for with ''Shazam!''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cinemablend.com/news/1838370/zachary-levi-compares-shazam-to-a-classic-tom-hanks-movie|title=Zachary Levi Compares Shazam To A Classic Tom Hanks Movie|last=Holmes|first=Adam|date=January 10, 2018|publisher=CinemaBlend|accessdate=January 10, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180130091322/https://www.cinemablend.com/news/1838370/zachary-levi-compares-shazam-to-a-classic-tom-hanks-movie|archive-date=January 30, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Warner Bros. stated that the film would be based on the 2012-2013 ''Shazam!'' backup feature from the ''[[Justice League]]'' comic book, by writer Geoff Johns and artist [[Gary Frank]], which told a modernized version of Shazam's origin.<ref name=\"Production\">{{cite web |url= https://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20180205006016/en/ |title= Production Starts on New Line Cinema's Magical Super Hero Action Adventure \"Shazam!\" |work=Business Wire |date= February 5, 2018 |accessdate= February 5, 2018 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20180208195750/https://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20180205006016/en/ |archive-date=February 8, 2018 |url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"GeoffJohnsPR\">{{cite web|url=https://www.warnerbros.com/studio/news/geoff-johns-expand-creative-role-becoming-full-time-writerproducer-film-television|title=GEOFF JOHNS TO EXPAND CREATIVE ROLE BECOMING A FULL-TIME WRITER/PRODUCER FOR FILM, TELEVISION AND MORE; EXCLUSIVE TO DC AND WARNER BROS.|work=Warner Bros. Entertainment|date=June 11, 2018|accessdate=June 12, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180614151940/https://www.warnerbros.com/studio/news/geoff-johns-expand-creative-role-becoming-full-time-writerproducer-film-television|archive-date=June 14, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\n===Pre-production===\nIn August 2017, director David F. Sandberg stated that the film would be the next to shoot in the DC universe,<ref name=\"HeroicHollywoodInterview\">{{cite news|last1=Peris|first1=Sebastian|title='Shazam' Director Says Earlier Versions Of The Script Featured Black Adam|url=https://heroichollywood.com/shazam-earlier-script-black-adam/|accessdate=August 17, 2017|publisher=Heroic Hollywood|date=August 16, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170909095302/https://heroichollywood.com/shazam-earlier-script-black-adam/|archive-date=September 9, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> and by the end of the month, it had begun [[Film and television production manager|pre-production]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Auger|first=Andrew|title=Shazam! Has Officially Begun Pre-Production|url=https://screenrant.com/shazam-movie-casting-filming/|accessdate=August 30, 2017|website=Screen Rant|date=August 29, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170902092820/http://screenrant.com/shazam-movie-casting-filming/|archive-date=September 2, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> By October 2017, cinematographer [[Maxime Alexandre]] and production designer Jennifer Spence, who previously worked with Sandberg on ''[[Annabelle: Creation]]'', were added to the production.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://omegaunderground.com/2017/10/19/shazam-adds-annabelle-2-cinematographer-production-designer/|title='Shazam!' Adds 'Annabelle 2' Cinematographer and Production Designer|last=Marc|first=Christopher|date=October 19, 2017|publisher=OmegaUnderground|accessdate=May 21, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180522111745/https://omegaunderground.com/2017/10/19/shazam-adds-annabelle-2-cinematographer-production-designer/|archive-date=May 22, 2018|url-status=dead|df=mdy-all}}</ref> The next month, ''[[Aquaman (film)|Aquaman]]'' stunt coordinator Kyle Gardiner was hired to work on the film's action sequences.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://omegaunderground.com/2017/11/24/shazam-hires-thor-ragnarok-aquaman-stunt-coordinator/|title='Shazam!' Hires 'Thor: Ragnarok' and 'Aquaman' Stunt Coordinator|last=Marc|first=Christopher|date=November 24, 2017|publisher=OmegaUnderground|accessdate=May 21, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180522111809/https://omegaunderground.com/2017/11/24/shazam-hires-thor-ragnarok-aquaman-stunt-coordinator/|archive-date=May 22, 2018|url-status=dead|df=mdy-all}}</ref> On January 12, 2018, the film's release date was announced as April 19, 2019, later moved to April 5.<ref name=\"ShazamDate\">{{cite news|last1=McNary|first1=Dave|title=DC\u2019s \u2018Shazam!\u2019 Gets 2019 Release Date|url=https://variety.com/2018/film/news/shazam-release-date-2019-1202663057/|accessdate=June 18, 2018|work=Variety|date=January 12, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180618152336/https://variety.com/2018/film/news/shazam-release-date-2019-1202663057/|archive-date=June 18, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\n===Casting===\n[[File:Zachary Levi by Gage Skidmore 4.jpg|thumb|upright|Zachary Levi at 2018 [[San Diego Comic-Con International]]]]\nBy September 2014, Dwayne Johnson was set to portray Black Adam in the film, but by July 2017, he had left the project to pursue a Black Adam solo film.<ref name=\"JohnsonCasted\" /><ref name=\"JohnsonLeaves\" /> In August 2017, the casting process for Shazam and other characters had begun. Sandberg had stated in an interview that instead of de-aging an actor using special effects or CGI, he would cast both a child actor and an adult actor for the role of the main character.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://heroichollywood.com/david-sandberg-shazam-annabelle-creation/|title=David Sandberg On Moving Right Into 'Shazam' From 'Annabelle: Creation'|last=Peris|first=Sebastian|date=August 25, 2017|publisher=Heroic Hollywood|accessdate=August 25, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170826072759/https://heroichollywood.com/david-sandberg-shazam-annabelle-creation/|archive-date=August 26, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> [[Zachary Levi]], [[John Cena]], [[Zane Holtz]], [[Jake McDorman]], [[Derek Theler]] and [[Billy Magnussen]] all met with and/or auditioned for Sandberg for the role of Shazam.<ref>{{cite magazine|last=Kit|first=Borys|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/shazam-star-zachary-levi-as-dc-hero-1049616|title=''Shazam!'' To Star Zachary Levi (EXCLUSIVE)|date=October 27, 2017|magazine=The Hollywood Reporter|accessdate=April 26, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180501061933/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/shazam-star-zachary-levi-as-dc-hero-1049616|archive-date=May 1, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nBy October 2017, Levi was cast in the titular role.<ref name=\"THRLevi\">{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/shazam-star-zachary-levi-as-dc-hero-1049616|title=DC's 'Shazam!' to Star Zachary Levi|last=Kit|first=Borys|date=October 27, 2017|publisher=TheHollywoodReporter|accessdate=October 27, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171028011957/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/shazam-star-zachary-levi-as-dc-hero-1049616|archive-date=October 28, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> In November, [[Grace Fulton]] joined the cast as [[Mary Marvel|Mary Bromfield]], one of Billy Batson's foster siblings.<ref>{{cite web |author=Michael Vassallo |url=https://heroichollywood.com/shazam-grace-fulton-mary-marvel/ |title=DC Comic's 'Shazam!' Director Confirms Grace Fulton Is Mary Marvel |publisher=Heroichollywood.com |date=September 1, 2017 |accessdate=December 16, 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171217014153/https://heroichollywood.com/shazam-grace-fulton-mary-marvel/ |archive-date=December 17, 2017 |url-status=live |df=mdy-all }}</ref> Fulton had previously worked with the same director on ''[[Annabelle: Creation]]''.<ref name=\"Fulton\">{{cite web|last=Kroll|first=Justin|url=https://variety.com/2017/film/news/grace-fulton-shazam-annabelle-creation-1202605521/amp/|title=''Annabelle Creation'' Actress Grace Fulton Joins ''Shazam''|date=November 2, 2017|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|accessdate=November 2, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171107011710/http://variety.com/2017/film/news/grace-fulton-shazam-annabelle-creation-1202605521/amp/|archive-date=November 7, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Later that month, [[Mark Strong]] was in final negotiations to play Dr. Sivana.<ref name=\"Strong\"/> Strong confirmed he would be playing the role by January 2018.<ref>{{cite web|last=Sky|first=Rick|url=http://www.contactmusic.net/mark-strong/news/mark-strong-spills-on-shazam-secrecy_5955962|title=Mark Strong spills on Shazam! secrecy|date=January 14, 2018|publisher=ContactMusic.net|accessdate=January 14, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180115001725/http://www.contactmusic.net/mark-strong/news/mark-strong-spills-on-shazam-secrecy_5955962|archive-date=January 15, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> By November 2017, [[Asher Angel]] was cast as the titular hero's teenage originator [[Billy Batson]].<ref name=\"auto\">{{cite magazine|last=Kit|first=Borys|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/shazam-asher-angel-star-as-billy-batson-dc-movie-1055189|title='Shazam!' Finds Its Billy Batson with 'Andi Mack' Actor|date=November 6, 2017|magazine=The Hollywood Reporter|accessdate=November 6, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171107070958/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/shazam-asher-angel-star-as-billy-batson-dc-movie-1055189|archive-date=November 7, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> In December, [[Jack Dylan Grazer]] was added as [[Captain Marvel Jr.|Freddy Freeman]], Batson's best friend.<ref name=\"Grazer\">{{cite magazine|last=N'Duka|first=Amanda|url=https://deadline.com/2017/12/it-jack-dylan-grazer-shazam-dc-movie-1202221613/|title=''It'' Actor Jack Dylan Grazer Joins ''Shazam''|date=December 6, 2017|magazine=Deadline|accessdate=December 6, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171207013228/http://deadline.com/2017/12/it-jack-dylan-grazer-shazam-dc-movie-1202221613/|archive-date=December 7, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Later that month, Jovan Armand, [[Ian Chen (actor)|Ian Chen]], Faithe Herman, and [[Cooper Andrews]] were cast as [[Marvel Family#Pedro|Pedro Pe\u00f1a]], [[Marvel Family#Eugene|Eugene Choi]], and [[Marvel Family#Darla|Darla Dudley]], with Andrews portraying Victor Vazquez, one of Billy Batson's foster parents.<ref name=\"Herman\">{{cite web|last=Outlaw|first=Kofi|url=https://comicbook.com/dc/2017/12/21/dc-shazam-movie-faithe-herman-darla-dudley/|title=DC's 'Shazam' Adds 'This Is Us' Actress Faithe Herman to Cast|date=December 21, 2017|publisher=Comicbook|accessdate=December 21, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171222091426/http://comicbook.com/dc/2017/12/21/dc-shazam-movie-faithe-herman-darla-dudley/|archive-date=December 22, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"ChenArmand\"/><ref name=\"Andrews\">{{cite magazine|last=N'Duka|first=Amanda|url=https://deadline.com/2017/12/the-walking-deads-cooper-andrews-shazam-new-line-1202229944/|title=''The Walking Dead's'' Cooper Andrews Joins ''Shazam''|date=December 19, 2017|magazine=Deadline|accessdate=December 19, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171221000304/http://deadline.com/2017/12/the-walking-deads-cooper-andrews-shazam-new-line-1202229944/|archive-date=December 21, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nBy January 2018, [[Ron Cephas Jones]] entered talks to play the role of the wizard [[Shazam (wizard)|Shazam]], who granted Batson his powers.<ref name=\"Jones\">{{cite web|last=Gonzalez|first=Umberto|url=https://www.thewrap.com/ron-cephas-jones-wizard-dc-superhero-shazam/|title='This Is Us' Star Ron Cephas Jones Circles Wizard Role in DC Superhero Film 'SHAZAM!' (Exclusive)|date=January 18, 2018|website=TheWrap|accessdate=January 18, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180119003130/https://www.thewrap.com/ron-cephas-jones-wizard-dc-superhero-shazam/|archive-date=January 19, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Later that month, Spanish actress Marta Milans joined the cast to play Rosa Vazquez, one of the foster parents at the home where Billy lives.<ref name=\"Milans\">{{cite magazine|last=Ramos|first=Dino-Ray|url=https://deadline.com/2018/01/shazam-marta-milans-zachary-levi-new-line-comic-book-superhero-film-1202266511/|title='Shazam!': Marta Milans Joins Zachary Levi In New Line Superhero Pic|date=January 22, 2018|magazine=Deadline|accessdate=January 22, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180123052819/http://deadline.com/2018/01/shazam-marta-milans-zachary-levi-new-line-comic-book-superhero-film-1202266511/|archive-date=January 23, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> By the end of January 2018, actress [[Lotta Losten]], the wife of director David F. Sandberg, revealed that she has a role in the film.<ref name=\"Losten\">{{cite tweet|user=lottalosten|last=Losten|first=Lotta|number=958799702094438406|title=Yes! I have a role in Shazam! I can finally say that!|date=January 31, 2018|accessdate=January 31, 2017}}</ref> On April 23, 2018, [[Ross Butler (actor)|Ross Butler]] was announced to have joined the cast.<ref name=\"Butler\">{{cite web|last=Kroll|first=Justin|url=https://variety.com/2018/film/news/riverdale-and-13-reasons-why-ross-butler-shazam-1202783587/|title='13 Reasons Why' Actor Ross Butler Joins DC's 'Shazam!'|date=April 23, 2018|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|accessdate=April 23, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180424112013/http://variety.com/2018/film/news/riverdale-and-13-reasons-why-ross-butler-shazam-1202783587/|archive-date=April 24, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> By July, [[Djimon Hounsou]] had replaced Jones as the wizard Shazam, due to Jones having scheduling conflicts.<ref name=\"Hounsou\">{{cite web |url=https://ew.com/movies/2018/07/10/djimon-hounsou-shazam-wizard |title=Exclusive: DC's 'Shazam!' casts 'Guardians' actor Djimon Hounsou as the Wizard |website=EW.com |language=en |access-date=2018-07-10 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180710194534/http://ew.com/movies/2018/07/10/djimon-hounsou-shazam-wizard/ |archive-date=July 10, 2018 |url-status=live |df=mdy-all }}</ref> [[Henry Cavill]] was in talks to reprise his role as [[Superman]] from previous DCEU films for a [[Cameo appearance|cameo]], but was unable to because of scheduling.<ref>{{cite web|first1=Tatiana|last1=Siegel|first2=Borys|last2=Kit|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/henry-cavill-as-superman-warner-bros-dc-universe-shake-up-1142306|title=Henry Cavill Out as Superman Amid Warner Bros.' DC Universe Shake-Up (Exclusive)|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=12 September 2018|accessdate=12 September 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180912191747/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/henry-cavill-as-superman-warner-bros-dc-universe-shake-up-1142306|archive-date=September 12, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\n===Filming===\nPrincipal photography for ''Shazam!'' began in [[Toronto]] and [[Hamilton, Ontario|Hamilton]], in Ontario, Canada on January 29, 2018, under the [[working title]] ''Franklin'',<ref>{{cite news|last=Mitchell|first=Bea|title=Superhero movie Shazam! to start filming in early 2018|url=http://www.digitalspy.com/movies/shazam/news/a838482/shazam-movie-2019-release-date-dceu-filming-2018/|accessdate=September 20, 2017|work=DigitalSpy|date=September 19, 2017|language=en|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170921174657/http://www.digitalspy.com/movies/shazam/news/a838482/shazam-movie-2019-release-date-dceu-filming-2018/|archive-date=September 21, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"FilmingCanada2\">{{cite web |url=http://omegaunderground.com/2017/09/14/working-title-shazam-movie-revealed/ |title=The Working Title of The 'Shazam!' Movie Revealed |last=Marc |first=Christopher |date=2017-09-14 |website=OmegaGround |access-date=2017-09-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170920103858/http://omegaunderground.com/2017/09/14/working-title-shazam-movie-revealed/ |archive-date=September 20, 2017 |url-status=live |df=mdy-all }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=David F. Sandberg on Instagram: Let's go!\u26a1\ufe0f|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/BeipkbDAYpp/|publisher=[[Instagram]]|accessdate=29 January 2018}}</ref> and wrapped by mid-May 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.toronto.ca/business-economy/industry-sector-support/film/current-productions-and-news/|title=Current Productions & News|publisher=Toronto.ca|accessdate=March 6, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180320211154/https://www.toronto.ca/business-economy/industry-sector-support/film/current-productions-and-news/|archive-date=March 20, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all|date=2017-08-07}}</ref> The film was set primarily in [[Philadelphia]], [[Pennsylvania]] and is firmly established within the DCEU.<ref name=\"Production\" /> Most of the production was shot at [[Pinewood Toronto Studios]], and also several public locations around the city, including the [[University of Toronto]], [[Woodbine Centre|Woodbine Shopping Centre]],<ref name=\"FilmingCanada\">{{cite web |url=http://omegaunderground.com/2017/09/18/confirmed-shazam-begins-filming-february-toronto/ |title=CONFIRMED: 'Shazam!' Begins Filming This February in Toronto |last=Williams |first=Caleb |date=2017-09-18 |website=OmegaGround |access-date=2017-09-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170930183308/http://omegaunderground.com/2017/09/18/confirmed-shazam-begins-filming-february-toronto/ |archive-date=September 30, 2017 |url-status=live |df=mdy-all }}</ref> and [[Hearn Generating Station]]. In early March 2018, filming took place at [[Fort York|Fort York National Historic Site]] in downtown Toronto.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cbr.com/shazam-set-video-costume-zachary-levi/|title=Shazam Set Video Shows Zachary Levi's DC Hero In Action|last=Cohen|first=Jason|date=March 6, 2018|publisher=CBR.com|accessdate=March 6, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180307151038/https://www.cbr.com/shazam-set-video-costume-zachary-levi/|archive-date=March 7, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> By early May 2018, Asher Angel, among other young cast members, had finished filming his part,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://screenrant.com/shazam-asher-angel-wraps-filming/|title=Shazam! Star Asher Angel Officially Wraps Filming|last=Hood|first=Cooper|date=May 7, 2018|publisher=ScreenRant.com|accessdate=May 7, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180508052829/https://screenrant.com/shazam-asher-angel-wraps-filming/|archive-date=May 8, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> and principal photography wrapped on May 11, 2018.<ref name=\"ShazamWrapped\">{{cite tweet|user=ponysmasher|last=Sandberg|first=David F.|number=9995017103894695936|title=That\u2019s a wrap on Shazam! Now onto months of post production.|date=May 11, 2018|accessdate=May 11, 2018}}</ref> Additional photography took place in Toronto between November and December 2018.<ref>{{cite web|last=Marc|first=Christopher|url=https://thegww.com/shazam-confirmed-to-get-two-weeks-of-reshoots-next-month-in-toronto/|title=''Shazam!'' Confirmed To Get Two Weeks Of Reshoots Next Month In Toronto|date=October 23, 2018|work=OmegaUnderground|publisher=Geeks WorldWide|accessdate=October 24, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181025071007/https://thegww.com/shazam-confirmed-to-get-two-weeks-of-reshoots-next-month-in-toronto/|archive-date=October 25, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://screenrant.com/shazam-movie-reshoots-schedule-extended/ |title=Shazam! Reshoots Reportedly Extended To Late December |date=2018-11-08 |website=ScreenRant |language=en-US |access-date=2018-11-10 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181110160107/https://screenrant.com/shazam-movie-reshoots-schedule-extended/ |archive-date=November 10, 2018 |url-status=live |df=mdy-all }}</ref> Scenes set at the [[Philadelphia Museum of Art]], and well as other location work such as footage of the [[skyline]] and [[Aerial photography|aerial shots]], were filmed in the city of [[Philadelphia]] in December 2018.<ref>{{cite web|last=HughE|first=Dillon|url=https://www.phillychitchat.com/2018/11/kendall.html|title='SHAZAM Films in Philly this Weekend, Kendall Jenner will be at Sixers Game Tonight|date=November 30, 2018|work=Philly ChitChat|accessdate=December 2, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181203055443/https://www.phillychitchat.com/2018/11/kendall.html|archive-date=December 3, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> ''Shazam!'' had a production budget of $90\u2013100 million (and about $102 million once post-production was complete), making it the least expensive DCEU film to-date.<ref name=\"Fuster\"/><ref name=preview/><ref>{{cite web|last=D'Alessandro|first=Anthony|url=https://deadline.com/2019/04/shazam-sequel-henry-gayden-screenwriter-returning-1202591584/|title=\u2018Shazam!\u2019 Scribe Henry Gayden To Pen Sequel|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=April 8, 2019|accessdate=April 20, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://screenrant.com/shazam-low-budget-suit-costs/|title=Shazam Budget Reportedly $80-$90M; Suits Didn't Cost $1M|date=2019-01-19|website=ScreenRant|language=en-US|access-date=2019-01-30}}</ref>\n\n===Post-production===\nDavid F. Sandberg's two-time collaborator Michel Aller served as the editor for ''Shazam!''.<ref name=\"Production\" /> Mike Wassel (''[[Hellboy II: The Golden Army]]'' and ''[[The Fast and the Furious]]'' franchise) and Kelvin McIlwain (''[[Aquaman (film)|Aquaman]]'') were the overall visual effects supervisors for the film. [[Technicolor SA|Technicolor]]'s VFX studios Mr. X (known for ''[[The Shape of Water]]'' and ''[[Tron: Legacy]]'') and [[Moving Picture Company]] (MPC) provided [[visual effects]]. [[Rodeo FX]], [[DNEG]], [[Digital Domain]], and [[Rise FX]] also worked on the VFX.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.artofvfx.com/shazam/|title=Art of VFX Shazam!|work=Art of VFX|date=January 21, 2019|accessdate=January 21, 2019}}</ref>\n\nMr. X was responsible for the scenes inside the Rock of Eternity, a dark cave-like environment where the Seven Deadly Sins are imprisoned. Four major sequences take place here, including the opening scene when a young Thad enters and is rejected as the new hero; when he returns as the older Dr. Sivana; when Billy enters and becomes Shazam; and the final showdown between Shazam and Sivana. VFX Supervisor Aaron Weintraub and the team at Mr. X were brought on board three months before shooting began in Toronto \u2013 where the town was abuzz with this exciting project and the mayor talked it up frequently. Weintraub found working with Sandberg and the filmmaking team to be an open, inviting, and collaborative experience.\n\nWhile the first level of the Rock of Eternity was an elaborately built set, everything above 20 feet was a digital environment extension, and within that was every type of visual effect \u2013 from bringing Shazam's chest bolt to life; to stunts with digi-doubles, people melting and statues crumbling; to the Orb and the Seven Deadly Sins flying in and out of it. the final showdown between Shazam and Sivana, in which the latter lets loose his gang of monsters, a 360 shot where seven creatures form from smoke unleashed from within.\n\nRodeo FX team deliver more than 130 shots to DC's latest entry, Shazam!. RodeoFX team recreate the city backdrop for the boardroom sequence. Using photographs of Pittsburgh, They built matte paintings of the city as seen from the boardroom, adding buildings and bustlings streets.\n\nFor the title sequence, They delivered the compositing of the company logos in the opening credits and built and animated the magic 8 ball in CG, adding frost and rays of light beam along matching the effects from the key subway scene from the film.\n\nDigital Domain worked on 26 VFX shots for the movie. Additionally Rise FX and DNEG provide visual effects for the film and the 3D conversion.\n\n==Music==\n{{main|Shazam! (soundtrack)}}\nOn July 21, 2018, [[Benjamin Wallfisch]] was announced as the composer for ''Shazam!'', marking his third collaboration with director David F. Sandberg after previously scoring Sandberg's ''[[Lights Out (2016 film)|Lights Out]]'' and ''[[Annabelle: Creation]]''.<ref>{{cite web |title=Benjamin Wallfisch to Score David F. Sandberg's 'Shazam!' |url=http://filmmusicreporter.com/2018/07/21/benjamin-wallfisch-to-score-david-f-sandbergs-shazam/ |publisher=Film Music Reporter |accessdate=July 21, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180722011452/http://filmmusicreporter.com/2018/07/21/benjamin-wallfisch-to-score-david-f-sandbergs-shazam/ |archive-date=July 22, 2018 |url-status=live |df=mdy-all }}</ref> Wallfisch had also provided additional music for ''[[Batman v Superman: Dawn of Justice]]'', the second film in the [[DC Extended Universe]].<ref>{{cite web |title='BATMAN V SUPERMAN: DAWN OF JUSTICE' - ORIGINAL MOTION PICTURE SOUNDTRACK RELEASE |url=https://www.benjaminwallfisch.com/news/behind-the-scenes-of-the-score-for-the-new-batman-v-superman-dawn-of-justice-movie/ |publisher=Benjaminwallfisch.com |accessdate=August 26, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180827075318/https://www.benjaminwallfisch.com/news/behind-the-scenes-of-the-score-for-the-new-batman-v-superman-dawn-of-justice-movie/ |archive-date=August 27, 2018 |url-status=live |df=mdy-all }}</ref>\n\nWallfisch cited [[John Williams]] and scores from 1980s [[Amblin Entertainment]] films as inspirations for ''Shazam!'', to match the tone of a film about \"an old-school superhero from the [[Golden Age of Comic Books|Golden Age]].\"<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://variety.com/2019/music/news/benjamin-wallfisch-composer-interview-1203181069/ |title=Composer Benjamin Wallfisch Scores High in Versatility With \u2018Hellboy,\u2019 \u2018Hostile,\u2019 \u2018Shazam!\u2019 |last=Burlingame |first=Jon |last2=Burlingame |first2=Jon |date=2019-04-04 |website=Variety |language=en |access-date=2019-04-22}}</ref> In writing the score, Wallfisch stated that he was \"picturing what might happen if a 14-year-old was put in front of a 100 piece orchestra and told there were no limits. I wanted the score to feel like it might have been written by an exuberant kid just having the time of his life with an orchestra.\"<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.dccomics.com/blog/2019/04/19/benjamin-wallfisch-sets-shazams-magic-to-music |title=Benjamin Wallfisch Sets Shazam!'s Magic to Music |last=Beedle |first=Tim |website=DCComics.com}}</ref>\n\n==Marketing==\n[[File:Zachary Levi, Asher Angel, Jack Dylan Grazer & David F. Sandberg by Gage Skidmore.jpg|thumb|(L:R) [[Zachary Levi]], [[Asher Angel]], [[Jack Dylan Grazer]] and [[David F. Sandberg]] promoting ''Shazam!'' at the 2018 [[San Diego Comic-Con|San Diego Comic Con International]]]]\n\nIn April 2018, a first look at ''Shazam!'' was shown at the [[ShoWest Convention|CinemaCon]] convention in [[Las Vegas]], [[Nevada]], as director David F. Sandberg introduced behind-the-scene footage.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Lang|first1=Brent|title=\u2018Aquaman\u2019 Footage Debuts at CinemaCon; \u2018Wonder Woman 2\u2019 Details Revealed|url=https://variety.com/2018/film/news/aquaman-footage-cinemacon-wonder-woman-2-1202785916/|accessdate=April 25, 2018|work=Variety|date=April 24, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180425022253/http://variety.com/2018/film/news/aquaman-footage-cinemacon-wonder-woman-2-1202785916/|archive-date=April 25, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Burlingame|first1=Russ|title=\u2018Shazam!\u2019 Footage Shown at CinemaCon|url=https://comicbook.com/dc/2018/04/25/shazam-footage-shown-at-cinemacon/|accessdate=April 25, 2018|work=Comicbook.com|date=April 24, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180426024009/http://comicbook.com/dc/2018/04/25/shazam-footage-shown-at-cinemacon/|archive-date=April 26, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> During an interview with [[Ryan Connolly (presenter)#Film Riot Mondays|Film Riot Podcast]] in June 2018, Sandberg stated that \"On this one, it was just like 'Yeah, I want this to be a classic superhero movie.' It takes place in the winter, so it's a lot of dark exteriors, but with a lot of colorful lights and stuff around them.\"<ref>{{cite web|last1=Williams|first1=Tommy|title=SHAZAM! Officially Confirmed to Take Place in Winter|url=https://geektyrant.com/news/shazam-officially-confirmed-to-take-place-in-winter|publisher=Geek Tyrant|accessdate=16 June 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180616153839/https://geektyrant.com/news/shazam-officially-confirmed-to-take-place-in-winter|archive-date=June 16, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> On July 21, 2018, the first teaser trailer was shown at [[San Diego Comic-Con]] during the Warner Bros. panel at Hall H, with Sandberg, Zachary Levi, Asher Angel, and Jack Dylan Grazer in attendance. The trailer was later released online.<ref name=\"ComicCon\">{{cite web |last1=Liptak |first1=Andrew |title=The first trailer for DC's Shazam is like Big, but with superheroes |url=https://www.theverge.com/2018/7/21/17598148/shazam-dc-comics-warner-bros-trailer-watch-san-diego-comic-con |website=theverge.com |accessdate=22 July 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180722105234/https://www.theverge.com/2018/7/21/17598148/shazam-dc-comics-warner-bros-trailer-watch-san-diego-comic-con |archive-date=July 22, 2018 |url-status=live |df=mdy-all |date=2018-07-21 }}</ref> It received a favorable response from journalists and audiences, who praised its humorous, zany tone.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Newby |first1=Richard |title=Why 'Shazam!' Was Biggest Surprise of Comic-Con |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/why-shazam-trailer-was-biggest-surprise-comic-con-1129342 |website=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |accessdate=August 13, 2018 |date=July 23, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180814001637/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/why-shazam-trailer-was-biggest-surprise-comic-con-1129342 |archive-date=August 14, 2018 |url-status=live |df=mdy-all }}</ref>\n\nNew footage from the film made its debut at [[Comic Con Experience|Brazil Comic Con]] (CCXP) in [[S\u00e3o Paulo]] on December 9, 2018 during the Warner Bros. studio panel, with the footage described for the attendees as action-packed.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Barnhardt |first1=Adam |title=New 'Shazam!' Footage Debuts at CCXP |url=https://comicbook.com/dc/2018/12/09/new-shazam-footage-ccxp/ |website=Comicbook.com |accessdate=January 4, 2019 |date=December 9, 2018}}</ref> A new trailer was released on March 4, and a three-minute sneak peek was included with the digital home media of ''[[Aquaman (film)|Aquaman]]''. At the [[STP 500]] on March 24, 2019, ''Shazam!'' was the primary sponsor of [[Aric Almirola]] and the #10 [[Ford Mustang]] in the [[Monster Energy NASCAR Cup Series]]. Almirola would go on to finish 9th after starting 2nd.<ref>{{cite web |title=Race Results|url=https://www.nascar.com/results/race_center/2019/monster-energy-nascar-cup-series/stp-500/stn/race/ |website=NASCAR.com |accessdate=March 24, 2019 |date=March 24, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Aric Almirola, a self described Batman fan, to drive Shazam car at Martinsville|url=http://tireball.com/nascar/2019/03/21/aric-almirola-a-self-described-batman-fan-to-drive-shazam-car-at-martinsville/ |website=Tireball.com |accessdate=March 24, 2019 |date=March 21, 2019}}</ref> Altogether the studio spent about $105 million promoting the film.<ref name=DeadlineProfit/>\n\n==Release==\n===Theatrical===\nOn March 13, 2019, [[Warner Bros. Pictures]] announced that they were teaming up with [[Fandango (company)|Fandango]] for exclusive preview screenings on March 23, two weeks before release, on 1,200 select screens and 40 exhibition circuits.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/03/shazam-fandango-early-preview-1202574896/|title=\u2018Shazam!\u2019 To Preview Two Weeks Before Opening Via Fandango Screening Program|author=Anthony D'Alessandro|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=March 13, 2019|accessdate=March 14, 2019}}</ref> ''Shazam!'' premiered in [[Toronto]] on March 15, 2019,<ref>{{cite news |title='Shazam' Toronto Premiere |url=https://etcanada.com/video/1459111491587/shazam-toronto-premiere/ |newspaper=[[Entertainment Tonight Canada]] |date=March 15, 2019 |accessdate=March 24, 2019}}</ref> and was theatrically released in the United States by [[Warner Bros. Pictures]] in [[RealD 3D]], [[Dolby Cinema]], [[4DX]], [[IMAX]], [[ScreenX]] and [[IMAX 3D]] Formats, in April 5, 2019.<ref name=\"ShazamDate\" />\n\n===Home media===\n''Shazam!'' was released on [[Digital distribution|digital download]] on July 2, 2019, and was released on [[Ultra HD Blu-ray]], [[Blu-ray]], and [[DVD]] on July 16. The digital and Blu-ray releases include behind-the-scenes featurettes, deleted scenes, and gag reels.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.slashfilm.com/shazam-blu-ray/|title=\u2018Shazam\u2019 Blu-ray and Digital Releases Arrive in July|date=2019-05-23|website=Slashfilm|language=en-US|access-date=2019-06-19}}</ref> The film was released on home medis in the United Kingdom on August 12, 2019/ also receive a release on Ultra HD Blu-ray, Blu-ray, and DVD on 12 August 2019, in the United Kingdom.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://shop.warnerbros.co.uk/shazam-blu-ray |title=Shazam! (Blu-ray) |website=shop.warnerbros.co.uk |language=en |access-date=2020-04-19}}</ref> {{asof|2020|4|10|df=US}}, ''Shazam!'' has made $8 million in DVD sales and $20.4 million in [[Blu-ray]] sales, totaling an estimated of $28.3 million in domestic video sales.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.the-numbers.com/movie/Shazam-(2019)#tab=summary |title=Shazam! (2019) |website=[[The Numbers (website)|The Numbers]] |accessdate=October 2, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n==Reception==\n===Box office===\n''Shazam!'' grossed $140.4 million in the United States and Canada, and $225.6 million in other territories, for a worldwide total of $366 million.<ref name=BOM/> It was estimated that the film needed to gross $235\u2013250 million worldwide in order to break even,<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/markhughes/2019/04/21/shazam-flies-high-to-300-million-worldwide/#2b51cb8a2ffd|title=\u2018Shazam' Flies High To $300+ Million Worldwide (Updated)|website=[[Forbes]]|author=Mark Hughes|date=April 21, 2019|accessdate=June 27, 2019}}</ref> and ''[[Deadline Hollywood]]'' calculated the film made a net profit of $74&nbsp;million, when factoring together all expenses and revenues.<ref name=DeadlineProfit>{{cite web|url= https://deadline.com/2020/04/shazam-box-office-profit-2019-zachary-levi-dc-comics-1202905779/ |title= \u2018Shazam!\u2019 Hits Grand Slam As No. 21 On Deadline\u2019s 2019 Most Valuable Blockbuster Tournament |first=Anthony|last=D'Alessandro|work=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=April 10, 2019|accessdate=April 10, 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn the United States and Canada, ''Shazam!'' was released alongside ''[[The Best of Enemies (2019 film)|The Best of Enemies]]'' and ''[[Pet Sematary (2019 film)|Pet Sematary]]'', and was projected to gross $40\u201350 million from 4,260 theaters in its opening weekend.<ref name=preview>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/03/shazam-pet-sematary-projected-box-office-opening-1202575628/|title=\u2018Shazam!\u2019 Looks To Strike Lightning With $45M Opening; \u2018Pet Sematary\u2019 Eyes Mid $20M+ \u2013 Early Tracking|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|author=Anthony D'Alessandro|date=March 14, 2019|accessdate=March 14, 2019}}</ref><ref name=VarietyBO>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2019/film/box-office/shazam-box-office-opening-weekend-pet-sematary-1203177258/|title=Box Office: \u2018Shazam!\u2019 Heads Toward $45 Million-Plus Opening Weekend|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|author=Rebecca Rubin|date=April 3, 2019|accessdate=April 3, 2019}}</ref> Two weeks before its release, the film grossed $3.3 million from Fandango advance screenings, higher than the $2.9 million made by fellow DCEU film ''[[Aquaman (film)|Aquaman]]'' the previous December.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/03/shazam-preview-record-box-office-1202581506/|title=\u2018Shazam!\u2019 Paid Previews Are Super At $3.3M, Beating \u2018Dragon 3\u2019, \u2018Aquaman\u2019 & More|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|author=Anthony D'Alessandro|date=March 24, 2019|accessdate=March 24, 2019}}</ref> It then made $5.9 million from Thursday night screenings on April 4, for a combined preview total of $9.2 million.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/04/shazam-pet-sematary-weekend-box-office-opening-1202588955/|title=\u2018Shazam!\u2019 Whams $5.9M In Thursday Night U.S. Previews For $9.2M Cume, Eyes $145M+ WW Launch \u2013 Friday AM Update|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|author=Anthony D'Alessandro|author2=Nancy Tartaglione|date=April 5, 2019|accessdate=April 5, 2019}}</ref> The film grossed a total of $20.5 million on its first day, including Thursday previews but not the March screenings. It went on to debut to $53.5 million, finishing first at the box office.<ref name=opening>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/04/shazam-opening-weekend-box-office-the-joker-pet-sematary-1202589627/|title=\u2018Shazam!\u2019 Shoots To Super $53M+ Opening, $56M+ With Previews; \u2018Pet Sematary\u2019 Purrs $25M \u2013 Sunday AM B.O. Final|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|author=Anthony D'Alessandro|date=April 7, 2019|accessdate=April 7, 2019}}</ref> In its second weekend the film made $25.1 million, retaining the top spot, before being dethroned by newcomer ''[[The Curse of La Llorona]]'' in its third weekend.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/04/hellboy-shazam-weekend-box-office-1202594516/|title=\u2018Shazam!\u2019 Still The Man With $23M+; \u2018Little\u2019 Grows Up; \u2018Hellboy\u2019 Cold With $12M+; \u2018After\u2019 Works Overseas \u2013 Midday B.O. Update|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|author=Anthony D'Alessandro|date=April 14, 2019|accessdate=April 14, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/04/the-curse-of-la-llorona-shazam-easter-weekend-box-office-2-1202598869/|title=Lowest Easter Weekend At The B.O. Since 2005 Despite $26M Purse Of \u2018La Llorona\u2019 \u2013 Saturday AM Update|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|author=Anthony D'Alessandro|date=April 21, 2019|accessdate=April 21, 2019}}</ref> In its fourth weekend, it made $5.8 million and finished fifth at the box office, including behind fellow superhero films ''[[Avengers: Endgame]]'' and ''[[Captain Marvel (film)|Captain Marvel]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/04/avengers-endgame-opening-weekend-box-office-record-1202602445/|title=Avengers: Endgame\u2019 Rests At $357M+ Opening Record; Eyes $33M+ Monday & Record $180M 2nd Frame; Weekend Biz Hits $401M+ High|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|last=D'Alessandro|first=Anthony|date=April 28, 2019|accessdate=April 28, 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn other territories, the film was released in 53 markets on Wednesday, April 3 and Thursday, April 4, and was projected to debut to $100\u2013120 million, for a global opening of $145\u2013170. In its first two days of international release the film made $15.7 million, finishing first in 48 of its 53 markets. It was then released in an additional 26 countries, including China, where it made $16.4 million on its first day. It went on to have an international debut of $102 million, and a global total of $158.6 million. It came in first in 60 of its 79 markets, with its highest-grossing being China ($43.4 million), Mexico ($10.6 million), Australia ($10.3 million), the UK ($15.3 million), Russia ($8.4 million) and Brazil ($8.7 million).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/04/shazam-opening-weekend-china-global-international-box-office-1202589047/|title=\u2018Shazam!\u2019 Strikes $102M Overseas Bow; \u2018Pet Sematary\u2019 Digs $17M; \u2018Dumbo\u2019, \u2018Us\u2019 Top $200M WW \u2013 International Box Office|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|author=Nancy Tartaglione|date=April 7, 2019|accessdate=April 7, 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Critical response===\nAt the [[review aggregator]] website [[Rotten Tomatoes]], the film holds an approval rating of 90% based on 385 reviews, with an [[Weighted arithmetic mean|average rating]] of 7.28/10. The website's critical consensus reads, \"An effortlessly entertaining blend of humor and heart, ''Shazam!'' is a superhero movie that never forgets the genre's real power: joyous wish fulfillment.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/shazam|title=Shazam! (2019)|last=|first=|date=|work=[[Rotten Tomatoes]]|publisher=[[Fandango Media]]|archive-url=|archive-date=|url-status=|accessdate=December 1, 2019}}</ref> On [[Metacritic]], it has a weighted average score of 71 out of 100, based on 53 critics, indicating \"generally favorable reviews.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.metacritic.com/movie/shazam!|title=Shazam! reviews|work=[[Metacritic]]|publisher=[[CBS Interactive]]|accessdate=June 5, 2019}}</ref> Audiences polled by [[CinemaScore]] gave the film an average grade of \"A\" on an A+ to F scale, while those at [[PostTrak]] gave it an overall positive score of 83% and a 61% \"definite recommend.\"<ref name=opening/>\n\nNick Allen of ''[[RogerEbert.com]]'' said that \"while ''Shazam!'' is goofier (and darker) than it may look, you'll wish its superhero came with a little more spark,\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rogerebert.com/reviews/shazam-2019|title=Shazam! Movie Review & Film Summary (2019) {{!}} Roger Ebert|last=Allen|first=Nick|website=www.rogerebert.com|language=en|access-date=2019-04-10}}</ref> while ''[[The Hollywood Reporter]]''{{'}}s Frank Scheck called the film \"''[[Big (film)|Big]]'' on steroids\" and praised the tone and performances.<ref>{{cite web|last=Scheck|first=Frank|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |date=March 23, 2019 |title='Shazam!': Film Review|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/review/shazam-review-1196387}}</ref> [[Alonso Duralde]] of ''[[TheWrap]]'' wrote, \"If the ''Wonder Woman'' and ''Aquaman'' movies represented DC Comics' first big-screen steps away from the austere color palette of the [[Zack Snyder]] movies, ''Shazam!'' takes us deeply into primary colors in a single bound... this new DC entry has a lovely lightness, both in the visuals and in its tone.\"<ref>{{cite web |author-link=Alonso Duralde|last=Duralde|first=Alonso|work=[[TheWrap]] |date=March 23, 2019 |title=\u2018Shazam!\u2019 Film Review: DC Comics Gets a Bouncy Burst of Big-Screen Ebullience|url=https://www.thewrap.com/shazam-film-review-dceu-2019/}}</ref>\n\nWriting for ''[[The A.V. Club]]'', [[Ignatiy Vishnevetsky]] gave the film a \"B\u2212\" and said: \"...while the story of an extremely overpowered champion rising to challenge a one-dimensionally sinister baddie might seem like the epitome of simplicity, ''Shazam!'' is still a modern-day tentpole blockbuster, overburdened with backstories for both hero and villain and subtexts that it can't (or won't) fully articulate.\"<ref name=\"avc\">{{cite web |author-link=Ignatiy Vishnevetsky |last=Vishnevetsky |first=Ignatiy |work=[[The A.V. Club]] |date=March 23, 2019 |title='Shazam!' Zaps an Old-Fashioned Superhero into a Blockbuster World |url=https://film.avclub.com/shazam-zaps-an-old-fashioned-superhero-into-a-blockbus-1833471014}}</ref> That publication followed up with a further consideration of [[masculinity]] in the film and the superhero genre generally, focusing on the transition of Billy Batson from an adolescent boy to a man with power and responsibility.<ref name=\"avcmasc\">{{cite news |url=https://film.avclub.com/shazam-redefines-masculinity-in-the-dc-universe-1833881774 |title=''Shazam!'' Redefines Masculinity in the DC Universe |last=Hassenger |first=Jesse |date=April 9, 2019 |accessdate=April 9, 2019 |newspaper=[[The A.V. Club]]}}</ref> Benjamin Lee of ''[[The Guardian]]'' gave the film 3/5 stars, specifying, \"The finale, while admirably self-contained and small-scale, grinds on for far too long, a boring escalation of anti-climaxes that cumulatively dull the intended emotional impact. It's a film in need of a tighter edit with a script in need of a sharper polish, an imperfect franchise-launcher that nonetheless represents significant progress for DC.\"<ref>{{cite web|last=Lee|first=Benjamin|work=[[The Guardian]] |date=March 23, 2019 |title=Shazam! review \u2013 kid-friendly DC adventure is enjoyably old school |url=https://www.theguardian.com/film/2019/mar/23/shazam-review-zachary-levi-dc-comics-universe}}</ref>\n\n===Accolades===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"width: 99%;\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" | Award\n! scope=\"col\" | Date of ceremony\n! scope=\"col\" | Category\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:35%;\" | Recipients\n! scope=\"col\" | Result\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\" | {{Abbr|Ref.|References}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:center;\"rowspan=\"2\"| [[Golden Trailer Awards]]\n| rowspan=\"2\"| May 29, 